nabled) |\n\n  Line 136: | Arch | C6 Memory compression / rollups (low-importance + low-recall → archive table) |\n\n  Line 204: - Consolidate 40 concepts → 17 (5 commands, 4 categories, 5 link types, 3 weight tiers)\n\n  Line 246: | Phase 0 | §2 indexes | 4 missing indexes added: `idx_memories_status_importance`, `idx_memories_created_at`, `idx_memories_last_recalled_at`, `idx_ctx_project_type_created` |\n\n  Line 247: | Phase 0 | §6 concurrency | `BEGIN IMMEDIATE`, atomic rename for registry, WAL semantics documented |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/08-mcp-tools.md:\n  Line 13: | `recall` | Search memories. FTS5 first, semantic fallback if needed. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/04-configuration.md:\n  Line 16:     \"semanticFallback\": true\n\n  Line 29: | `semanticFallback` | `true` | Fall back to embedding search when FTS returns no results |\n\n  Line 37: 3. **Default fallback** — `$CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA/openltm.db`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/02-how-it-works.md:\n  Line 36:                      |  | memories_fts    | |\n\n  Line 49: | **Session Start** | `SessionStart` hook injects top memories (importance ≥ 3) + project context (goals, decisions, gotchas) |\n\n  Line 60: Memories have half-lives based on importance. Stale knowledge fades; critical knowledge never does.\n\n  Line 73: score = importance × confidence × decay_factor\n\n  Line 78: This is intentional. A gotcha you never revisited for six months probably no longer applies. If you want it permanent, set `importance: 5`. If you're not sure, set `importance: 3` and let it ride.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/