language query. FTS5 + semantic fallback. Filters: project, category, importance. Primary read path. |\n\n  Line 114: | `learn` | Store a new memory. Required: text, category. Optional: importance, project, tags. Auto-redacts secrets on write. |\n\n  Line 148: | `SessionStart` | Claude Code session opens | Resolve project from registry, regenerate `context-summary.md`, inject up to ~60 lines of context, inject importance-5 globals + top-15 project memories. |\n\n  Line 181: plus the **importance** scalar (1-5) used to gate global injection.\n\n  Line 200: - **Given** the same project, **when** session starts, **then** importance-5 global memories are also injected.\n\n  Line 208: - **Given** the same DB, **when** the FTS5 query returns < 3 results, **then** semantic fallback runs and merges results, deduplicated by id.\n\n  Line 209: - **Given** I pass `category: \"gotcha\"`, **when** I recall, **then** only gotchas are returned.\n\n  Line 216: - **Given** I have just made a decision, **when** I run `/openltm:memory learn \"X because Y\" --category architecture`, **then** the memory is persisted and an id is returned in under 200 ms.\n\n  Line 230: - **Given** a memory has not been recalled in 90 days and has importance < 3, **when** decay scoring runs, **then** its rank score is multiplied by a decay factor < 1.\n\n  Line 231: - **Given** importance == 5, **when** decay scoring runs, **then** the score is **not** decayed.\n\n  Line 232: - **Given** I run `/openltm:health`, **when** it executes, **then** it reports: total memories, count by category, count by decay bucket (fresh / aging / stale), and top-5 staleness candidates with ids.\n\n  Line 297: - **Given** a repo with N commits, **when** I run the GitLearn skill flow (\"git learn\"), **then** it analyzes commit messages and diffs, proposes candidate memories with category + importance + text.\n\n  Line 302: **As** Pat after the same gotcha bites in two projects, **I want** to promote it to global with importance 5.\n\n  Line 305: - **Given** a project-scoped `gotcha` context item, **when** I run `/openltm:memory learn \"<text>\" --category gotcha --importance 5`, **then** it lands in the global `memories` table.\n\n  Line 306: - **Given** importance 5, **when** any future SessionStart fires, **then** this memory is in the global injection regardless of project.\n\n  Line 313: - **Given** memories with relations exist, **when** I open the UI, **then** I see nodes (memories) and edges (relations) with category-based coloring.\n\n  Line 340: ### G-C — Auto-categorization on `learn`\n\n  Line 341: Today the user picks `--category`. Use a lightweight classifier (heuristic or model\n\n  Line 342: call) to suggest category and importance. **Why magnificent:** drops the friction of\n\n  Line 346: Explicit failure-mode category, surfaced when a recall would otherwise suggest the\n\n  Line 350: ### G-E — Project-scoped semantic embeddings\n\n  Line 351: Today recall is FTS5 + semantic fallback at the global level. A per-project embedding\n\n  Line 381: For each result, a one-line \"why this ranked here\" (FTS hit, semantic similarity,\n\n  Line 382: recency boost, importance boost). Powers debuggability of bad recalls. **Why\n\n  Line 383: magnificent:** the user can teach the system by adjusting importance instead of\n\n  Line 393: can write into LTM with proper category and source tag. **Why magnificent:** LTM\n\n  Line 398: overlay, force-directed clustering by category, click-through to invoking session.\n\n  Line 417:   own tools or a deterministic fallback. No bundled ML runtime.\n\n  Line 461: - **D3.** Cross-project memory reuse rate: % of importance-5 globals injected into\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md:\n  Line 50:     System(ltm, \"LTM Plugin\", \"Persistent semantic memory, context restore, decay, learn/recall\")\n\n  Line 96:     ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\", \"SQLite WAL\", \"memories, context_items, tags, memory_relations, memories_fts, settings\")\n\n  Line 98:     ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\", \"Markdown fallback file\", \"Human-readable context snapshot regenerated on PreCompact\")\n\n  Line 146:     Component(recall, \"Recall Engine\", \"src/db.ts:recall\", \"FTS5 query → semantic fallback → merge → rank by importance/recency/decay\")\n\n  Line 163:   Rel(learn, db, \"INSERT memories, INSERT memories_fts via trigger\")\n\n  Line 208: | Recall Engine | Search ranking | Merging FTS5 + semantic results, applying decay |\n\n  Line 209: | Learn Engine | Write path | Dedup, redaction, importance/category enforcement |\n\n  Line 242:   Start->>DB: SELECT goal, decisions, gotchas, progress (project) + importance-5 globals\n\n  Line 251:     MCP->>DB: semantic fallback (embedding similarity)\n\n  Line 254:   MCP->>MCP: apply decay scoring + importance boost\n\n  Line 260:   Claude->>MCP: learn({ content, category, importance, project })\n\n  Line 262:   MCP->>DB: INSERT memories (trigger writes memories_fts)\n\n  Line 268:   Pre->>Sum: write context-summary.md (~60 lines, fallback)\n\n  Line 289: | learn | — | DB (memories, memories_fts via trigger) | Reject duplicate dedup_key; redact before write |\n\n  Line 290: | PreCompact | DB | context-summary.md | If write fails, post-compact session loses fallback only |\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 215 matches (115 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":215,"truncated":true},"title":"why_ranked|categor|BM25|semantic|fallback|fts|hybrid|recency|importance","time":{"start":1780924912103,"end":1780924912130}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ac7c34af796bfe6016a26c1effd6c819686f94907808b3788"}},"id":"prt_ea76591e3001P7HL3YGGF2ZsHD","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","messageID":"msg_ea76572080010CYaHDo92Ni1gS"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780924912818,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"id":"prt_ea76594ad0010sWJY67OY81pXQ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fcf1d1d2108399e291c0845331d1441cf6e7fffb","messageID":"msg_ea76572080010CYaHDo92Ni1gS","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":43470,"input":8364,"output":170,"reasoning":120,"cache":{"write":0,"read":34816}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780924915078,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"id":"prt_ea7659d85001cNkFe3pd6GT22Y","messageID":"msg_ea765964c0018NPwXaY45vNhEv","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","snapshot":"b7e9e476215c831fa44a90aa371896253aa833b1","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780924926137,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_klwM5fenSmGmVSkiOb282pmV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/02-how-it-works.md","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/02-how-it-works.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # How It Works\n2: \n3: The one-page tour. The [Architecture](03-architecture.md) doc is the 1000-line deep-dive; this is the 30-second version that gets you oriented before you read it.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## The shape of memory\n8: \n9: ```\n10: +---------------------------------------------------------------+\n11: |                        Claude Code                            |\n12: |                                                               |\n13: |  +-------------------+  +-----------+  +------------------+   |\n14: |  | 4 Commands        |  | 5 Skills  |  | 4 Claude Code    |   |\n15: |  | /openltm:memory       |  | Continu-  |  |    hooks         |   |\n16: |  | /openltm:project      |  | ousLearn  |  | SessionStart     |   |\n17: |  | /openltm:health       |  | LtmServer |  | UpdateContext    |   |\n18: |  | /openltm:admin        |  | GitLearn  |  | EvaluateSession  |   |\n19: |  |                   |  | Learned   |  | PreCompact       |   |\n20: |  +--------+----------+  +-----+-----+  +------------------+   |\n21: |           +-------------------+---------+                     |   |\n22: |                               |                            |   |\n23: |                      +--------v--------+                   |   |\n24: |                      |   ltm MCP       |                   |   |\n25: |                      |   server        |                   |   |\n26: |                      +--------+--------+                   |   |\n27: +-------------------------------|------------------------------+\n28:                                 |\n29:                      +----------v-----------+\n30:                      |       openltm.db         |\n31:                      |  +-----------------+ |\n32:                      |  | memories        | |\n33:                      |  | context_items   | |\n34:                      |  | memory_relations| |\n35:                      |  | tags            | |\n36:                      |  | memories_fts    | |\n37:                      |  +-----------------+ |\n38:                      +----------------------+\n39: ```\n40: \n41: Three surfaces — **commands** (you talk), **skills** (Claude's prompt workflows), **hooks** (the lifecycle events) — all funnel through the **MCP server** into a single SQLite database.\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Session lifecycle\n46: \n47: | Phase | What Happens |\n48: |-------|-------------|\n49: | **Session Start** | `SessionStart` hook injects top memories (importance ≥ 3) + project context (goals, decisions, gotchas) |\n50: | **During Work** | Use `/openltm:memory recall` before tasks, `/openltm:memory learn` after discoveries. MCP tools called automatically. |\n51: | **Session Stop** | `UpdateContext` saves progress. `EvaluateSession` extracts patterns from the transcript. |\n52: | **Pre-Compact** | `PreCompact` snapshots context to `context-summary.md` so it survives compaction. |\n53: \n54: You never have to remember any of this. The hooks are wired on install. If you want the playbook, see [Hooks](06-hooks.md).\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Memory decay\n59: \n60: Memories have half-lives based on importance. Stale knowledge fades; critical knowledge never does.\n61: \n62: | Importance | Half-Life | Behavior |\n63: |:----------:|:---------:|----------|\n64: | 5 | Forever | Never decays. Injected every session. |\n65: | 4 | 180 days | Long-lived architectural decisions |\n66: | 3 | 90 days | Standard patterns and workflows |\n67: | 2 | 30 days | Short-lived context |\n68: | 1 | 14 days | Ephemeral — fades fast if not accessed |\n69: \n70: The score formula:\n71: \n72: ```\n73: score = importance × confidence × decay_factor\n74: ```\n75: \n76: A memory's `decay_factor` shrinks toward 0 as it ages past its half-life. Below 0.25, it's **soft-deprecated** — still returned by `recall` if you ask explicitly, but no longer auto-injected at session start.\n77: \n78: This is intentional. A gotcha you never revisited for six months probably no longer applies. If you want it permanent, set `importance: 5`. If you're not sure, set `importance: 3` and let it ride.\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## Project structure\n83: \n84: ```\n85: src/                  MCP server, DB layer, embeddings, graph traversal\n86: hooks/src/            4 Claude Code hooks (SessionStart, UpdateContext, EvaluateSession, PreCompact) + 1 git hook (GitCommit)\n87: hooks/lib/            Shared hook utilities (resolveProject, llmExtract)\n88: hooks/bin/            run-hook.sh — bun resolver wrapper for stripped-PATH environments\n89: hooks/hooks.json      Claude Code hook registrations (auto-wired on install)\n90: commands/             4 slash commands\n91: skills/               5 Claude Code skills\n92: scripts/              install-wiring.ts, update-wiring.ts\n93: graph-app/            Next.js memory graph visualizer (port 7332)\n94: migrations/           SQL schema migrations\n95: .claude-plugin/       Plugin manifest (plugin.json)\n96: docs/                 This documentation\n97: CLAUDE.md             Loaded by Claude — tool reference\n98: CHANGELOG.md          Version history\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Where to go from here\n104: \n105: - [Architecture](03-architecture.md) — C4 diagrams, ADRs, schema, migration path, the works\n106: - [DB Spec](internal/DB-SPEC.md) — every table, every column, every index\n107: - [Configuration](04-configuration.md) — knobs that control decay, injection, and embedding\n108: - [Hooks](06-hooks.md) — what fires when\n109: - [PRD](internal/PRD.md) — product vision and roadmap\n\n(End of file - total 109 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/AGENTS.md\n# OpenLTM — agent instructions\n\nHost-agnostic guidance for any AI coding agent working in this repo (Claude Code reads `CLAUDE.md`; OpenCode and other tools read this file). OpenLTM gives agents persistent semantic memory across sessions via a local SQLite database.\n\n## Using memory\n\nThe memory tools are exposed over MCP as `recall`, `learn`, `context`, `forget`, `relate` (in Claude Code, prefixed `mcp__plugin_openltm_memory__*`). The goal is automatic knowledge retrieval and capture — use judgment, not a call before every sentence.\n\n- **`recall`** before a non-trivial task, or when the work touches past decisions or an unfamiliar area. Skip for trivial one-liners.\n- **`learn`** after discovering a non-obvious pattern, architectural decision, or gotcha worth keeping across sessions.\n- **`context`** at session start or when switching projects, to restore goals, decisions, and gotchas.\n\nCategories: `preference | architecture | gotcha | pattern | workflow | constraint`. Importance `5` never decays; everything else ages out as it goes unused.\n\n## Working in this repo\n\n- **Runtime is Bun**, not npm/node. Use `bun`, `bunx`, `bun test`.\n- **Tests + typecheck must pass**: `bun test && bun run typecheck`.\n- **Version bumps are mandatory** on any change — `bun run bump <version>` then `bun run verify-version` (it gates all version sources: `package.json`, `.claude-plugin/plugin.json`, `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json`, every `packages/*/package.json`, and the README badge).\n- **No secrets, no database files** in commits. `data/*.db*` is gitignored; keep it that way.\n\n## Shipping to OpenCode\n\nInstalling OpenLTM into OpenCode (`bunx @rohirik/openltm-core --opencode`) does two things: registers the `@rohirik/opencode-ltm` plugin in `opencode.json`, and deploys the bundled customization (agents, skills, plugins) from the package's `assets/opencode/` into the user's OpenCode config directory.\n\n## Releasing\n\nTag-driven and tokenless: bump versions, add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry, then `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin main vX.Y.Z`. The tag fires the Release and Publish workflows; npm packages publish via OIDC trusted publishing with provenance — no stored token. Full detail in `CONTRIBUTING.md`.\n\n## Docs\n\nUser-facing docs are in [`docs/`](docs/README.md); internal design specs in [`docs/internal/`](docs/internal/README.md).\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"# How It Works\n\nThe one-page tour. The [Architecture](03-architecture.md) doc is the 1000-line deep-dive; this is the 30-second version that gets you oriented before you read it.\n\n---\n\n## The shape of memory\n\n```\n+---------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                        Claude Code                            |\n|                                                               |\n|  +-------------------+  +-----------+  +------------------+   |\n|  | 4 Commands        |  | 5 Skills  |  | 4 Claude Code    |   |\n|  | /openltm:memory       |  | Continu-  |  |    hooks         |   |\n|  | /openltm:project      |  | ousLearn  |  | SessionStart     |   |\n|  | /openltm:health       |  | LtmServer |  | UpdateContext    |   |\n|  | /openltm:admin        |  | GitLearn  |  | EvaluateSession  |   |\n|  |                   |  | Learned   |  | PreCompact       |   |\n|  +--------+----------+  +-----+-----+  +------------------+   |","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/AGENTS.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/02-how-it-works.md","text":"# How It Works\n\nThe one-page tour. The [Architecture](03-architecture.md) doc is the 1000-line deep-dive; this is the 30-second version that gets you oriented before you read it.\n\n---\n\n## The shape of memory\n\n```\n+---------------------------------------------------------------+\n|                        Claude Code                            |\n|                                                               |\n|  +-------------------+  +-----------+  +------------------+   |\n|  | 4 Commands        |  | 5 Skills  |  | 4 Claude Code    |   |\n|  | /openltm:memory       |  | Continu-  |  |    hooks         |   |\n|  | /openltm:project      |  | ousLearn  |  | SessionStart     |   |\n|  | /openltm:health       |  | LtmServer |  | UpdateContext    |   |\n|  | /openltm:admin        |  | GitLearn  |  | EvaluateSession  |   |\n|  |                   |  | Learned   |  | PreCompact       |   |\n|  +--------+----------+  +-----+-----+  +------------------+   |\n|           +-------------------+---------+                     |   |\n|                               |                            |   |\n|                      +--------v--------+                   |   |\n|                      |   ltm MCP       |                   |   |\n|                      |   server        |                   |   |\n|                      +--------+--------+                   |   |\n+-------------------------------|------------------------------+\n                                |\n                     +----------v-----------+\n                     |       openltm.db         |\n                     |  +-----------------+ |\n                     |  | memories        | |\n                     |  | context_items   | |\n                     |  | memory_relations| |\n                     |  | tags            | |\n                     |  | memories_fts    | |\n                     |  +-----------------+ |\n                     +----------------------+\n```\n\nThree surfaces — **commands** (you talk), **skills** (Claude's prompt workflows), **hooks** (the lifecycle events) — all funnel through the **MCP server** into a single SQLite database.\n\n---\n\n## Session lifecycle\n\n| Phase | What Happens |\n|-------|-------------|\n| **Session Start** | `SessionStart` hook injects top memories (importance ≥ 3) + project context (goals, decisions, gotchas) |\n| **During Work** | Use `/openltm:memory recall` before tasks, `/openltm:memory learn` after discoveries. MCP tools called automatically. |\n| **Session Stop** | `UpdateContext` saves progress. `EvaluateSession` extracts patterns from the transcript. |\n| **Pre-Compact** | `PreCompact` snapshots context to `context-summary.md` so it survives compaction. |\n\nYou never have to remember any of this. The hooks are wired on install. If you want the playbook, see [Hooks](06-hooks.md).\n\n---\n\n## Memory decay\n\nMemories have half-lives based on importance. Stale knowledge fades; critical knowledge never does.\n\n| Importance | Half-Life | Behavior |\n|:----------:|:---------:|----------|\n| 5 | Forever | Never decays. Injected every session. |\n| 4 | 180 days | Long-lived architectural decisions |\n| 3 | 90 days | Standard patterns and workflows |\n| 2 | 30 days | Short-lived context |\n| 1 | 14 days | Ephemeral — fades fast if not accessed |\n\nThe score formula:\n\n```\nscore = importance × confidence × decay_factor\n```\n\nA memory's `decay_factor` shrinks toward 0 as it ages past its half-life. Below 0.25, it's **soft-deprecated** — still returned by `recall` if you ask explicitly, but no longer auto-injected at session start.\n\nThis is intentional. A gotcha you never revisited for six months probably no longer applies. If you want it permanent, set `importance: 5`. If you're not sure, set `importance: 3` and let it ride.\n\n---\n\n## Project structure\n\n```\nsrc/                  MCP server, DB layer, embeddings, graph traversal\nhooks/src/            4 Claude Code hooks (SessionStart, UpdateContext, EvaluateSession, PreCompact) + 1 git hook (GitCommit)\nhooks/lib/            Shared hook utilities (resolveProject, llmExtract)\nhooks/bin/            run-hook.sh — bun resolver wrapper for stripped-PATH environments\nhooks/hooks.json      Claude Code hook registrations (auto-wired on install)\ncommands/             4 slash commands\nskills/               5 Claude Code skills\nscripts/              install-wiring.ts, update-wiring.ts\ngraph-app/            Next.js memory graph visualizer (port 7332)\nmigrations/           SQL schema migrations\n.claude-plugin/       Plugin manifest (plugin.json)\ndocs/                 This documentation\nCLAUDE.md             Loaded by Claude — tool reference\nCHANGELOG.md          Version history\n```\n\n---\n\n## Where to go from here\n\n- [Architecture](03-architecture.md) — C4 diagrams, ADRs, schema, migration path, the works\n- [DB Spec](internal/DB-SPEC.md) — every table, every column, every index\n- [Configuration](04-configuration.md) — knobs that control decay, injection, and embedding\n- [Hooks](06-hooks.md) — what fires when\n- [PRD](internal/PRD.md) — product vision and roadmap","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":109,"totalLines":109,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/02-how-it-works.md","time":{"start":1780924926119,"end":1780924926133}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c5a652d3b65a9a9016a26c1fe0b98819185008db47d12481e"}},"id":"prt_ea765c8a4001U2OloN2d8lU3a9","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","messageID":"msg_ea765964c0018NPwXaY45vNhEv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780924926159,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7ziVu2s5cxgy3E2ICRggzyNZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","offset":130,"limit":150},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n130: This level breaks the **MCP server** and **hook runners** into their internal\n131: components. The command/skill layer is intentionally not decomposed — markdown specs\n132: have no internal components.\n133: \n134: ### 3.1 MCP Server components\n135: \n136: ```mermaid\n137: C4Component\n138:   title MCP Server — Components\n139: \n140:   Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"MCP client\")\n141:   ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n142: \n143:   Container_Boundary(mcp, \"MCP Server (src/mcp-server.ts)\") {\n144:     Component(transport, \"STDIO Transport\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\", \"JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\")\n145:     Component(toolreg, \"Tool Registry\", \"McpServer.tool()\", \"Declares recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph with Zod schemas\")\n146:     Component(recall, \"Recall Engine\", \"src/db.ts:recall\", \"FTS5 query → semantic fallback → merge → rank by importance/recency/decay\")\n147:     Component(learn, \"Learn Engine\", \"src/db.ts:learn\", \"Validate → redact secrets → dedup-key check → insert → return id\")\n148:     Component(ctxmerge, \"Context Merge\", \"src/db.ts:getContextMerge + src/context.ts:getItems\", \"Build the goal+decisions+progress+gotchas envelope for SessionStart\")\n149:     Component(graphtrav, \"Graph Traversal\", \"src/graph.ts:traverseGraph\", \"BFS over memory_relations; powers graph and visualization feed\")\n150:     Component(formatter, \"Compact Formatter\", \"src/mcp-server.ts:compact/strip\", \"Strips embedding blob, truncates content to keep MCP responses small\")\n151:     Component(config, \"Config Reader\", \"src/config.ts\", \"Reads plugin config; respects mcp.enabled flag\")\n152:   }\n153: \n154:   Rel(claude, transport, \"JSON-RPC\")\n155:   Rel(transport, toolreg, \"dispatch\")\n156:   Rel(toolreg, recall, \"recall\")\n157:   Rel(toolreg, learn, \"learn\")\n158:   Rel(toolreg, ctxmerge, \"context, context_items\")\n159:   Rel(toolreg, graphtrav, \"graph\")\n160:   Rel(toolreg, formatter, \"shape response\")\n161:   Rel(toolreg, config, \"feature flag check\")\n162:   Rel(recall, db, \"FTS5 + base table queries\")\n163:   Rel(learn, db, \"INSERT memories, INSERT memories_fts via trigger\")\n164:   Rel(ctxmerge, db, \"SELECT context_items + memories\")\n165:   Rel(graphtrav, db, \"SELECT memory_relations\")\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### 3.2 Hook Runners components\n169: \n170: ```mermaid\n171: C4Component\n172:   title Hook Runners — Components\n173: \n174:   Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"Spawns hooks per lifecycle event\")\n175:   ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n176:   ContainerDb(reg, \"registry.json\")\n177:   ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\")\n178: \n179:   Container_Boundary(hooks, \"Hook Runners (hooks/*.ts)\") {\n180:     Component(start, \"SessionStart hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Resolve project from cwd → registry; rebuild context-summary.md; emit injection block\")\n181:     Component(pre, \"PreCompact hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Pull all 4 context types from DB; serialize to context-summary.md (~60 line cap)\")\n182:     Component(eval, \"EvaluateSession hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Score session; identify candidate insights; (proposes / auto-writes per OQ4)\")\n183:     Component(update, \"UpdateContext hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Append progress entries; trim to last 20; bump last-touched timestamps\")\n184:     Component(resolver, \"Project Resolver\", \"shared util\", \"cwd → project name via registry; auto-register on first touch\")\n185:     Component(injector, \"Context Injector\", \"shared util\", \"Compose ## Restored Project Context block; truncate to ~60 lines + footer\")\n186:     Component(redact, \"Secret Redactor\", \"shared util\", \"Pattern-match API keys, JWTs, AWS keys; replace with [REDACTED:type]\")\n187:   }\n188: \n189:   Rel(claude, start, \"spawn(SessionStart)\")\n190:   Rel(claude, pre, \"spawn(PreCompact)\")\n191:   Rel(claude, eval, \"spawn(EvaluateSession)\")\n192:   Rel(claude, update, \"spawn(UpdateContext)\")\n193:   Rel(start, resolver, \"resolve\")\n194:   Rel(start, injector, \"build block\")\n195:   Rel(start, db, \"SELECT context_items + globals\")\n196:   Rel(start, reg, \"read / auto-register\")\n197:   Rel(pre, db, \"SELECT all context types\")\n198:   Rel(pre, summary, \"write\")\n199:   Rel(eval, db, \"INSERT memories (or pending)\")\n200:   Rel(eval, redact, \"scrub before write\")\n201:   Rel(update, db, \"INSERT progress; UPDATE timestamps\")\n202: ```\n203: \n204: **Component responsibilities at a glance**\n205: \n206: | Component | Responsibility | Single source of truth for |\n207: |-----------|----------------|---------------------------|\n208: | Recall Engine | Search ranking | Merging FTS5 + semantic results, applying decay |\n209: | Learn Engine | Write path | Dedup, redaction, importance/category enforcement |\n210: | Context Merge | Read path for SessionStart | Envelope shape (goal + decisions + progress + gotchas) |\n211: | Project Resolver | cwd → project | Authoritative map; auto-registration |\n212: | Secret Redactor | Pattern scrub | Redaction policy, called from learn + EvaluateSession |\n213: | Context Injector | Format injection | 60-line budget, footer rendering |\n214: | Compact Formatter | MCP response shaping | Stripping embedding blob, content truncation |\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## 4. Data Flow: Full Session Lifecycle\n219: \n220: This is the canonical end-to-end flow that ties every container and component together.\n221: A \"session\" spans from Claude Code launch in a project cwd through to clean exit (or\n222: compaction-triggered restart). The diagram shows one full cycle.\n223: \n224: ```mermaid\n225: sequenceDiagram\n226:   autonumber\n227:   actor Dev as Developer\n228:   participant Claude as Claude Code Harness\n229:   participant Start as SessionStart hook\n230:   participant Reg as registry.json\n231:   participant DB as openltm.db (SQLite)\n232:   participant MCP as MCP Server\n233:   participant Eval as EvaluateSession hook\n234:   participant Pre as PreCompact hook\n235:   participant Update as UpdateContext hook\n236:   participant Sum as context-summary.md\n237: \n238:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session start ---\n239:   Dev->>Claude: cd into project, launch Claude Code\n240:   Claude->>Start: spawn(SessionStart, stdin=cwd)\n241:   Start->>Reg: resolve(cwd) → project_name (auto-register if new)\n242:   Start->>DB: SELECT goal, decisions, gotchas, progress (project) + importance-5 globals\n243:   Start-->>Claude: stdout = \"## Restored Project Context\\n...\" (≤ 60 lines)\n244:   Claude-->>Dev: render injected block\n245: \n246:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Recall before deciding ---\n247:   Dev->>Claude: prompt that requires past context\n248:   Claude->>MCP: recall({ query, project })\n249:   MCP->>DB: FTS5(MATCH) → ranked rowids\n250:   alt FTS5 returns < 3 results\n251:     MCP->>DB: semantic fallback (embedding similarity)\n252:     MCP->>MCP: merge + dedup by id\n253:   end\n254:   MCP->>MCP: apply decay scoring + importance boost\n255:   MCP-->>Claude: top-N memories (compact, embedding-stripped)\n256:   Claude-->>Dev: answer informed by recalled context\n257: \n258:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Work + learn ---\n259:   Dev->>Claude: makes a decision; runs /openltm:memory learn\n260:   Claude->>MCP: learn({ content, category, importance, project })\n261:   MCP->>MCP: redact secrets; compute dedup_key\n262:   MCP->>DB: INSERT memories (trigger writes memories_fts)\n263:   MCP-->>Claude: { id }\n264: \n265:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Mid-session: compaction ---\n266:   Claude->>Pre: spawn(PreCompact)\n267:   Pre->>DB: SELECT all 4 context types for project\n268:   Pre->>Sum: write context-summary.md (~60 lines, fallback)\n269:   Pre-->>Claude: ack\n270:   Claude->>Claude: compact transcript\n271:   Note over Claude: Next assistant turn re-reads context-summary.md if needed\n272: \n273:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session end ---\n274:   Claude->>Update: spawn(UpdateContext)\n275:   Update->>DB: INSERT progress; trim oldest > 20; UPDATE last_touched\n276:   Update-->>Claude: ack\n277:   Claude->>Eval: spawn(EvaluateSession)\n278:   Eval->>DB: scan transcript-derived signals; propose / write candidate insights\n279:   Eval-->>Claude: ack\n\n(Showing lines 130-279 of 1075. Use offset=280 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"This level breaks the **MCP server** and **hook runners** into their internal\ncomponents. The command/skill layer is intentionally not decomposed — markdown specs\nhave no internal components.\n\n### 3.1 MCP Server components\n\n```mermaid\nC4Component\n  title MCP Server — Components\n\n  Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"MCP client\")\n  ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n\n  Container_Boundary(mcp, \"MCP Server (src/mcp-server.ts)\") {\n    Component(transport, \"STDIO Transport\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\", \"JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\")\n    Component(toolreg, \"Tool Registry\", \"McpServer.tool()\", \"Declares recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph with Zod schemas\")\n    Component(recall, \"Recall Engine\", \"src/db.ts:recall\", \"FTS5 query → semantic fallback → merge → rank by importance/recency/decay\")\n    Component(learn, \"Learn Engine\", \"src/db.ts:learn\", \"Validate → redact secrets → dedup-key check → insert → return id\")\n    Component(ctxmerge, \"Context Merge\", \"src/db.ts:getContextMerge + src/context.ts:getItems\", \"Build the goal+decisions+progress+gotchas envelope for SessionStart\")\n    Component(graphtrav, \"Graph Traversal\", \"src/graph.ts:traverseGraph\", \"BFS over memory_relations; powers graph and visualization feed\")","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","text":"This level breaks the **MCP server** and **hook runners** into their internal\ncomponents. The command/skill layer is intentionally not decomposed — markdown specs\nhave no internal components.\n\n### 3.1 MCP Server components\n\n```mermaid\nC4Component\n  title MCP Server — Components\n\n  Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"MCP client\")\n  ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n\n  Container_Boundary(mcp, \"MCP Server (src/mcp-server.ts)\") {\n    Component(transport, \"STDIO Transport\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\", \"JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\")\n    Component(toolreg, \"Tool Registry\", \"McpServer.tool()\", \"Declares recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph with Zod schemas\")\n    Component(recall, \"Recall Engine\", \"src/db.ts:recall\", \"FTS5 query → semantic fallback → merge → rank by importance/recency/decay\")\n    Component(learn, \"Learn Engine\", \"src/db.ts:learn\", \"Validate → redact secrets → dedup-key check → insert → return id\")\n    Component(ctxmerge, \"Context Merge\", \"src/db.ts:getContextMerge + src/context.ts:getItems\", \"Build the goal+decisions+progress+gotchas envelope for SessionStart\")\n    Component(graphtrav, \"Graph Traversal\", \"src/graph.ts:traverseGraph\", \"BFS over memory_relations; powers graph and visualization feed\")\n    Component(formatter, \"Compact Formatter\", \"src/mcp-server.ts:compact/strip\", \"Strips embedding blob, truncates content to keep MCP responses small\")\n    Component(config, \"Config Reader\", \"src/config.ts\", \"Reads plugin config; respects mcp.enabled flag\")\n  }\n\n  Rel(claude, transport, \"JSON-RPC\")\n  Rel(transport, toolreg, \"dispatch\")\n  Rel(toolreg, recall, \"recall\")\n  Rel(toolreg, learn, \"learn\")\n  Rel(toolreg, ctxmerge, \"context, context_items\")\n  Rel(toolreg, graphtrav, \"graph\")\n  Rel(toolreg, formatter, \"shape response\")\n  Rel(toolreg, config, \"feature flag check\")\n  Rel(recall, db, \"FTS5 + base table queries\")\n  Rel(learn, db, \"INSERT memories, INSERT memories_fts via trigger\")\n  Rel(ctxmerge, db, \"SELECT context_items + memories\")\n  Rel(graphtrav, db, \"SELECT memory_relations\")\n```\n\n### 3.2 Hook Runners components\n\n```mermaid\nC4Component\n  title Hook Runners — Components\n\n  Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"Spawns hooks per lifecycle event\")\n  ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n  ContainerDb(reg, \"registry.json\")\n  ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\")\n\n  Container_Boundary(hooks, \"Hook Runners (hooks/*.ts)\") {\n    Component(start, \"SessionStart hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Resolve project from cwd → registry; rebuild context-summary.md; emit injection block\")\n    Component(pre, \"PreCompact hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Pull all 4 context types from DB; serialize to context-summary.md (~60 line cap)\")\n    Component(eval, \"EvaluateSession hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Score session; identify candidate insights; (proposes / auto-writes per OQ4)\")\n    Component(update, \"UpdateContext hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Append progress entries; trim to last 20; bump last-touched timestamps\")\n    Component(resolver, \"Project Resolver\", \"shared util\", \"cwd → project name via registry; auto-register on first touch\")\n    Component(injector, \"Context Injector\", \"shared util\", \"Compose ## Restored Project Context block; truncate to ~60 lines + footer\")\n    Component(redact, \"Secret Redactor\", \"shared util\", \"Pattern-match API keys, JWTs, AWS keys; replace with [REDACTED:type]\")\n  }\n\n  Rel(claude, start, \"spawn(SessionStart)\")\n  Rel(claude, pre, \"spawn(PreCompact)\")\n  Rel(claude, eval, \"spawn(EvaluateSession)\")\n  Rel(claude, update, \"spawn(UpdateContext)\")\n  Rel(start, resolver, \"resolve\")\n  Rel(start, injector, \"build block\")\n  Rel(start, db, \"SELECT context_items + globals\")\n  Rel(start, reg, \"read / auto-register\")\n  Rel(pre, db, \"SELECT all context types\")\n  Rel(pre, summary, \"write\")\n  Rel(eval, db, \"INSERT memories (or pending)\")\n  Rel(eval, redact, \"scrub before write\")\n  Rel(update, db, \"INSERT progress; UPDATE timestamps\")\n```\n\n**Component responsibilities at a glance**\n\n| Component | Responsibility | Single source of truth for |\n|-----------|----------------|---------------------------|\n| Recall Engine | Search ranking | Merging FTS5 + semantic results, applying decay |\n| Learn Engine | Write path | Dedup, redaction, importance/category enforcement |\n| Context Merge | Read path for SessionStart | Envelope shape (goal + decisions + progress + gotchas) |\n| Project Resolver | cwd → project | Authoritative map; auto-registration |\n| Secret Redactor | Pattern scrub | Redaction policy, called from learn + EvaluateSession |\n| Context Injector | Format injection | 60-line budget, footer rendering |\n| Compact Formatter | MCP response shaping | Stripping embedding blob, content truncation |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Data Flow: Full Session Lifecycle\n\nThis is the canonical end-to-end flow that ties every container and component together.\nA \"session\" spans from Claude Code launch in a project cwd through to clean exit (or\ncompaction-triggered restart). The diagram shows one full cycle.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n  autonumber\n  actor Dev as Developer\n  participant Claude as Claude Code Harness\n  participant Start as SessionStart hook\n  participant Reg as registry.json\n  participant DB as openltm.db (SQLite)\n  participant MCP as MCP Server\n  participant Eval as EvaluateSession hook\n  participant Pre as PreCompact hook\n  participant Update as UpdateContext hook\n  participant Sum as context-summary.md\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session start ---\n  Dev->>Claude: cd into project, launch Claude Code\n  Claude->>Start: spawn(SessionStart, stdin=cwd)\n  Start->>Reg: resolve(cwd) → project_name (auto-register if new)\n  Start->>DB: SELECT goal, decisions, gotchas, progress (project) + importance-5 globals\n  Start-->>Claude: stdout = \"## Restored Project Context\\n...\" (≤ 60 lines)\n  Claude-->>Dev: render injected block\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Recall before deciding ---\n  Dev->>Claude: prompt that requires past context\n  Claude->>MCP: recall({ query, project })\n  MCP->>DB: FTS5(MATCH) → ranked rowids\n  alt FTS5 returns < 3 results\n    MCP->>DB: semantic fallback (embedding similarity)\n    MCP->>MCP: merge + dedup by id\n  end\n  MCP->>MCP: apply decay scoring + importance boost\n  MCP-->>Claude: top-N memories (compact, embedding-stripped)\n  Claude-->>Dev: answer informed by recalled context\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Work + learn ---\n  Dev->>Claude: makes a decision; runs /openltm:memory learn\n  Claude->>MCP: learn({ content, category, importance, project })\n  MCP->>MCP: redact secrets; compute dedup_key\n  MCP->>DB: INSERT memories (trigger writes memories_fts)\n  MCP-->>Claude: { id }\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Mid-session: compaction ---\n  Claude->>Pre: spawn(PreCompact)\n  Pre->>DB: SELECT all 4 context types for project\n  Pre->>Sum: write context-summary.md (~60 lines, fallback)\n  Pre-->>Claude: ack\n  Claude->>Claude: compact transcript\n  Note over Claude: Next assistant turn re-reads context-summary.md if needed\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session end ---\n  Claude->>Update: spawn(UpdateContext)\n  Update->>DB: INSERT progress; trim oldest > 20; UPDATE last_touched\n  Update-->>Claude: ack\n  Claude->>Eval: spawn(EvaluateSession)\n  Eval->>DB: scan transcript-derived signals; propose / write candidate insights\n  Eval-->>Claude: ack","lineStart":130,"lineEnd":279,"totalLines":1075,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","time":{"start":1780924926122,"end":1780924926145}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c5a652d3b65a9a9016a26c1fe0ba0819184bbcb9ddb1eccb0"}},"id":"prt_ea765c8a8001akoVNFHFgmH0Hm","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","messageID":"msg_ea765964c0018NPwXaY45vNhEv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780924926159,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7UR90qXxSyX6EpXQ9m7BgIGA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /**\n2:  * db.ts — Global long-term memory (learned insights, patterns, preferences)\n3:  * Replaces skills/learned/*.md with structured SQLite + FTS5.\n4:  */\n5: import type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\n6: import { existsSync, mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from \"fs\";\n7: import { join } from \"path\";\n8: import { normalizeKey } from \"./dedup.js\";\n9: import { getDb, DB_PATH, configure as configureDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\n10: import { enqueueEmbedding } from \"./queue/index.js\";\n11: import { notifyLtm, notifyMemoryAdded } from \"./events/index.js\";\n12: import { scrubSecrets } from \"./secretsScrubber.js\";\n13: import { insertProvenance, insertAudit, snapshotMemory, listProvenanceBatch } from \"./dao/provenanceAudit.js\";\n14: import type { ProvenanceSourceType } from \"./dao/types.js\";\n15: import type { LtmCoreConfig } from \"./adapterTypes.js\";\n16: import { tmpdir } from \"os\";\n17: \n18: export { DB_PATH };\n19: /** Adapters can override via configureDocs() or LtmCoreConfig.docsDir. */\n20: let DOCS_DIR = join(tmpdir(), \"ltm-docs\");\n21: \n22: export function configureDocs(dir: string): void { DOCS_DIR = dir; }\n23: \n24: export function configureCore(config: LtmCoreConfig): void {\n25:   configureDb(config);\n26:   if (config.docsDir) DOCS_DIR = config.docsDir;\n27: }\n28: \n29: export type MemoryCategory = \"preference\" | \"architecture\" | \"gotcha\" | \"pattern\" | \"workflow\" | \"constraint\";\n30: export type RelationshipType = \"supports\" | \"contradicts\" | \"refines\" | \"depends_on\" | \"related_to\" | \"supersedes\";\n31: \n32: export interface Memory {\n33:   id: number;\n34:   content: string;\n35:   category: MemoryCategory;\n36:   importance: number;\n37:   confidence: number;\n38:   source: string | null;\n39:   project_scope: string | null;\n40:   dedup_key: string | null;\n41:   created_at: string;\n42:   last_confirmed_at: string;\n43:   last_used_at: string;\n44:   confirm_count: number;\n45:   status: \"active\" | \"pending\" | \"deprecated\" | \"superseded\";\n46:   first_recalled_at?: string;\n47:   last_recalled_at?: string;\n48:   recall_count?: number;\n49:   superseded_by?: number;\n50:   superseded_at?: string;\n51:   workspace_id?: string;\n52:   agent_id?: string;\n53:   decay_score?: number;\n54: }\n55: \n56: export interface MemoryRelation {\n57:   id: number;\n58:   source_memory_id: number;\n59:   target_memory_id: number;\n60:   relationship_type: RelationshipType;\n61:   created_at: string;\n62: }\n63: \n64: export interface MemoryWithRelations extends Memory {\n65:   tags: string[];\n66:   relations: Array<{ memory: Memory; relationship_type: RelationshipType; direction: \"outgoing\" | \"incoming\" }>;\n67:   /** Populated only when recall({ includeProvenance: true }) is requested. */\n68:   provenance?: import(\"./dao/types.js\").ProvenanceRow[];\n69:   /** Score breakdown + temperature — always populated by recall(). */\n70:   explainer?: import(\"./recall/explainer.js\").RecallExplainer;\n71: }\n72: \n73: export interface LearnInput {\n74:   content: string;\n75:   /** Short human-readable label (≤60 chars). Agent-supplied; falls back to heuristic. */\n76:   title?: string;\n77:   category: MemoryCategory;\n78:   importance?: number;\n79:   confidence?: number;\n80:   source?: string;\n81:   project_scope?: string;\n82:   workspace_id?: string;\n83:   agent_id?: string;\n84:   tags?: string[];\n85:   relate_to?: Array<{ id: number; relationship_type: RelationshipType }>;\n86:   /** Skip regenerating docs/memory-long-term.md (use during bulk imports) */\n87:   skipExport?: boolean;\n88:   /** Audit/provenance — all optional; safe to omit from existing callers. */\n89:   actor?: string;\n90:   sessionId?: string;\n91:   provenanceSourceType?: ProvenanceSourceType;\n92:   provenanceSourceRef?: string;\n93:   provenanceMetadata?: string;\n94: }\n95: \n96: export interface LearnResult {\n97:   action: \"created\" | \"reinforced\";\n98:   id: number;\n99:   confirm_count: number;\n100: }\n101: \n102: export interface RecallInput {\n103:   since?: string;\n104:   until?: string;\n105:   sort_by?: \"relevance\" | \"created\" | \"last_recalled\" | \"recall_count\";\n106: \n107:   query?: string;\n108:   tags?: string[];\n109:   category?: MemoryCategory;\n110:   project?: string;\n111:   limit?: number;\n112:   workspace_id?: string;\n113:   agent_id?: string;\n114:   /** When true, each result includes a `provenance` array. Off by default to preserve latency. */\n115:   includeProvenance?: boolean;\n116: }\n117: \n118: \n119: /** Derive a short title from content when none is agent-supplied. */\n120: export function deriveTitle(content: string): string {\n121:   const trimmed = content.trim();\n122:   const dot = trimmed.indexOf('.');\n123:   const nl = trimmed.indexOf('\\n');\n124:   const boundary = [dot, nl].filter(i => i > 1 && i <= 60).sort((a, b) => a - b)[0];\n125:   if (boundary !== undefined) return trimmed.slice(0, boundary).trim();\n126:   if (trimmed.length <= 60) return trimmed;\n127:   const cut = trimmed.slice(0, 57);\n128:   const lastSpace = cut.lastIndexOf(' ');\n129:   return (lastSpace > 20 ? cut.slice(0, lastSpace) : cut) + '…';\n130: }\n131: \n132: function tryAudit(fn: () => void): void {\n133:   try { fn(); } catch (e) { process.stderr.write(`[audit] write failed: ${e}\\n`); }\n134: }\n135: \n136: function upsertTag(db: Database, name: string): number {\n137:   db.run(`INSERT OR IGNORE INTO tags (name) VALUES (?)`, [name]);\n138:   return db.query<{ id: number }, [string]>(`SELECT id FROM tags WHERE name=?`).get(name)!.id;\n139: }\n140: \n\n(Showing lines 1-140 of 780. Use offset=141 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * db.ts — Global long-term memory (learned insights, patterns, preferences)\n * Replaces skills/learned/*.md with structured SQLite + FTS5.\n */\nimport type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\nimport { existsSync, mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from \"fs\";\nimport { join } from \"path\";\nimport { normalizeKey } from \"./dedup.js\";\nimport { getDb, DB_PATH, configure as configureDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\nimport { enqueueEmbedding } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { notifyLtm, notifyMemoryAdded } from \"./events/index.js\";\nimport { scrubSecrets } from \"./secretsScrubber.js\";\nimport { insertProvenance, insertAudit, snapshotMemory, listProvenanceBatch } from \"./dao/provenanceAudit.js\";\nimport type { ProvenanceSourceType } from \"./dao/types.js\";\nimport type { LtmCoreConfig } from \"./adapterTypes.js\";\nimport { tmpdir } from \"os\";\n\nexport { DB_PATH };\n/** Adapters can override via configureDocs() or LtmCoreConfig.docsDir. */\nlet DOCS_DIR = join(tmpdir(), \"ltm-docs\");","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","text":"/**\n * db.ts — Global long-term memory (learned insights, patterns, preferences)\n * Replaces skills/learned/*.md with structured SQLite + FTS5.\n */\nimport type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\nimport { existsSync, mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from \"fs\";\nimport { join } from \"path\";\nimport { normalizeKey } from \"./dedup.js\";\nimport { getDb, DB_PATH, configure as configureDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\nimport { enqueueEmbedding } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { notifyLtm, notifyMemoryAdded } from \"./events/index.js\";\nimport { scrubSecrets } from \"./secretsScrubber.js\";\nimport { insertProvenance, insertAudit, snapshotMemory, listProvenanceBatch } from \"./dao/provenanceAudit.js\";\nimport type { ProvenanceSourceType } from \"./dao/types.js\";\nimport type { LtmCoreConfig } from \"./adapterTypes.js\";\nimport { tmpdir } from \"os\";\n\nexport { DB_PATH };\n/** Adapters can override via configureDocs() or LtmCoreConfig.docsDir. */\nlet DOCS_DIR = join(tmpdir(), \"ltm-docs\");\n\nexport function configureDocs(dir: string): void { DOCS_DIR = dir; }\n\nexport function configureCore(config: LtmCoreConfig): void {\n  configureDb(config);\n  if (config.docsDir) DOCS_DIR = config.docsDir;\n}\n\nexport type MemoryCategory = \"preference\" | \"architecture\" | \"gotcha\" | \"pattern\" | \"workflow\" | \"constraint\";\nexport type RelationshipType = \"supports\" | \"contradicts\" | \"refines\" | \"depends_on\" | \"related_to\" | \"supersedes\";\n\nexport interface Memory {\n  id: number;\n  content: string;\n  category: MemoryCategory;\n  importance: number;\n  confidence: number;\n  source: string | null;\n  project_scope: string | null;\n  dedup_key: string | null;\n  created_at: string;\n  last_confirmed_at: string;\n  last_used_at: string;\n  confirm_count: number;\n  status: \"active\" | \"pending\" | \"deprecated\" | \"superseded\";\n  first_recalled_at?: string;\n  last_recalled_at?: string;\n  recall_count?: number;\n  superseded_by?: number;\n  superseded_at?: string;\n  workspace_id?: string;\n  agent_id?: string;\n  decay_score?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface MemoryRelation {\n  id: number;\n  source_memory_id: number;\n  target_memory_id: number;\n  relationship_type: RelationshipType;\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface MemoryWithRelations extends Memory {\n  tags: string[];\n  relations: Array<{ memory: Memory; relationship_type: RelationshipType; direction: \"outgoing\" | \"incoming\" }>;\n  /** Populated only when recall({ includeProvenance: true }) is requested. */\n  provenance?: import(\"./dao/types.js\").ProvenanceRow[];\n  /** Score breakdown + temperature — always populated by recall(). */\n  explainer?: import(\"./recall/explainer.js\").RecallExplainer;\n}\n\nexport interface LearnInput {\n  content: string;\n  /** Short human-readable label (≤60 chars). Agent-supplied; falls back to heuristic. */\n  title?: string;\n  category: MemoryCategory;\n  importance?: number;\n  confidence?: number;\n  source?: string;\n  project_scope?: string;\n  workspace_id?: string;\n  agent_id?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  relate_to?: Array<{ id: number; relationship_type: RelationshipType }>;\n  /** Skip regenerating docs/memory-long-term.md (use during bulk imports) */\n  skipExport?: boolean;\n  /** Audit/provenance — all optional; safe to omit from existing callers. */\n  actor?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  provenanceSourceType?: ProvenanceSourceType;\n  provenanceSourceRef?: string;\n  provenanceMetadata?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface LearnResult {\n  action: \"created\" | \"reinforced\";\n  id: number;\n  confirm_count: number;\n}\n\nexport interface RecallInput {\n  since?: string;\n  until?: string;\n  sort_by?: \"relevance\" | \"created\" | \"last_recalled\" | \"recall_count\";\n\n  query?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  category?: MemoryCategory;\n  project?: string;\n  limit?: number;\n  workspace_id?: string;\n  agent_id?: string;\n  /** When true, each result includes a `provenance` array. Off by default to preserve latency. */\n  includeProvenance?: boolean;\n}\n\n\n/** Derive a short title from content when none is agent-supplied. */\nexport function deriveTitle(content: string): string {\n  const trimmed = content.trim();\n  const dot = trimmed.indexOf('.');\n  const nl = trimmed.indexOf('\\n');\n  const boundary = [dot, nl].filter(i => i > 1 && i <= 60).sort((a, b) => a - b)[0];\n  if (boundary !== undefined) return trimmed.slice(0, boundary).trim();\n  if (trimmed.length <= 60) return trimmed;\n  const cut = trimmed.slice(0, 57);\n  const lastSpace = cut.lastIndexOf(' ');\n  return (lastSpace > 20 ? cut.slice(0, lastSpace) : cut) + '…';\n}\n\nfunction tryAudit(fn: () => void): void {\n  try { fn(); } catch (e) { process.stderr.write(`[audit] write failed: ${e}\\n`); }\n}\n\nfunction upsertTag(db: Database, name: string): number {\n  db.run(`INSERT OR IGNORE INTO tags (name) VALUES (?)`, [name]);\n  return db.query<{ id: number }, [string]>(`SELECT id FROM tags WHERE name=?`).get(name)!.id;\n}\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":140,"totalLines":780,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","time":{"start":1780924926103,"end":1780924926147}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c5a652d3b65a9a9016a26c1fe0b6c8191a26df0a6ff9bcf98"}},"id":"prt_ea765c87b0010mbqUGaoyfqQbQ","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","messageID":"msg_ea765964c0018NPwXaY45vNhEv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780924926159,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_08DBGyAvHeHEqAIPQmMWyWbh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","offset":417,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n417: export async function recall(input: RecallInput = {}): Promise<MemoryWithRelations[]> {\n418:   const db = getDb();\n419:   const limit = input.limit ?? 10;\n420: \n421:   let ids: Set<number> | null = null;\n422:   const ftsRanks = new Map<number, number>();      // id → normalized [0,1]\n423:   const semanticScores = new Map<number, number>(); // id → cosine similarity [0,1]\n424: \n425:   if (input.query) {\n426:     // Sanitize for FTS5: quote each token (prevents reserved-word errors) and join with OR\n427:     const ftsQuery = input.query\n428:       .trim()\n429:       .split(/\\s+/)\n430:       .filter(Boolean)\n431:       .map(t => `\"${t.replace(/\"/g, '\"\"')}\"`)\n432:       .join(\" OR \");\n433:     const ftsResults = db.query<{ rowid: number; rank: number }, [string]>(\n434:       `SELECT rowid, rank FROM memories_fts WHERE memories_fts MATCH ? ORDER BY rank LIMIT 50`\n435:     ).all(ftsQuery);\n436:     ids = new Set<number>();\n437:     for (const r of ftsResults) {\n438:       ids.add(r.rowid);\n439:       // FTS5 BM25 rank is a negative number (closer to 0 = better).\n440:       // Math.exp maps it to (0, 1] where 1 is a perfect match.\n441:       ftsRanks.set(r.rowid, Math.exp(r.rank));\n442:     }\n443: \n444:     // Semantic fallback: if FTS5 returned fewer results than requested, augment with vector search\n445:     if (ids.size < limit) {\n446:       const { readConfigSync } = await import(\"./config.js\");\n447:       const cfg = readConfigSync();\n448:       const semanticEnabled = cfg.ltm?.semanticFallback !== false; // default true\n449:       if (semanticEnabled) {\n450:         try {\n451:           const { getSimilarMemories } = await import(\"./embeddings.js\");\n452:           const semantic = await getSimilarMemories(input.query, limit * 2, 0.5);\n453:           for (const m of semantic) {\n454:             ids.add(m.id);\n455:             semanticScores.set(m.id, m.similarity);\n456:           }\n457:         } catch (err) {\n458:           process.stderr.write(`[recall] Semantic fallback failed: ${err}\\n`);\n459:         }\n460:       }\n461:     }\n462:   }\n463: \n464:   if (input.tags && input.tags.length > 0) {\n465:     const tagIds = input.tags.map(t => {\n466:       const row = db.query<{ id: number }, [string]>(`SELECT id FROM tags WHERE name=?`).get(t.toLowerCase());\n467:       return row?.id;\n468:     }).filter((id): id is number => id !== undefined);\n469: \n470:     if (tagIds.length > 0) {\n471:       const placeholders = tagIds.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n472:       const tagMemIds = db.query<{ memory_id: number }, number[]>(\n473:         `SELECT DISTINCT memory_id FROM memory_tags WHERE tag_id IN (${placeholders})`\n474:       ).all(...tagIds).map(r => r.memory_id);\n475: \n476:       const tagSet = new Set(tagMemIds);\n477:       ids = ids ? new Set([...ids].filter(id => tagSet.has(id))) : tagSet;\n478:     }\n479:   }\n480: \n481:   const conditions: string[] = [];\n482:   const params: (string | number | null)[] = [];\n483: \n484:   if (ids !== null) {\n485:     if (ids.size === 0) return [];\n486:     const placeholders = [...ids].map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n487:     conditions.push(`id IN (${placeholders})`);\n488:     params.push(...ids);\n489:   }\n490: \n491:   if (input.category) {\n492:     conditions.push(\"category=?\");\n493:     params.push(input.category);\n494:   }\n495: \n496:   if (input.project) {\n497:     conditions.push(\"(project_scope IS NULL OR project_scope=?)\");\n498:     params.push(input.project);\n499:   }\n500: \n501:   if (input.workspace_id) {\n502:     conditions.push(\"(workspace_id IS NULL OR workspace_id=?)\");\n503:     params.push(input.workspace_id);\n504:   }\n505:   if (input.agent_id) {\n506:     conditions.push(\"(agent_id IS NULL OR agent_id=?)\");\n507:     params.push(input.agent_id);\n508:   }\n509: \n510:   conditions.push(\"status = 'active'\");\n511: \n512:   if (input.since) {\n513:     conditions.push(\"(created_at > ? OR last_recalled_at > ?)\");\n514:     params.push(input.since, input.since);\n515:   }\n516:   if (input.until) {\n517:     conditions.push(\"(created_at < ? OR last_recalled_at < ?)\");\n518:     params.push(input.until, input.until);\n519:   }\n520: \n521:   const where = `WHERE ${conditions.join(\" AND \")}`;\n522:   // Explicit columns — excludes embedding blob (~260 KB/row) from hot recall path.\n523:   // Use getById(id, { withEmbedding: true }) when the blob is needed.\n524:   // default sort (no query): ORDER BY decay_score DESC pushed to SQL → O(log N)\n525:   const defaultSqlSort = (!input.sort_by || input.sort_by === \"relevance\") && ids === null;\n526:   const orderBy = defaultSqlSort ? \"ORDER BY decay_score DESC\" : \"\";\n527:   const rows = db.query<Memory, typeof params>(\n528:     `SELECT id, content, category, importance, confidence, source, project_scope, dedup_key,\n529:             created_at, last_confirmed_at, last_used_at, confirm_count, status,\n530:             first_recalled_at, last_recalled_at, recall_count, superseded_by, superseded_at,\n531:             workspace_id, agent_id, decay_score\n532:      FROM memories ${where} ${orderBy} LIMIT ${limit}`\n533:   ).all(...params);\n534: \n535:   let sorted: typeof rows;\n536:   if (defaultSqlSort) {\n537:     sorted = rows; // already ordered by decay_score DESC in SQL\n538:   } else if (input.sort_by === \"created\") {\n539:     sorted = rows.sort((a, b) => new Date(b.created_at).getTime() - new Date(a.created_at).getTime());\n540:   } else if (input.sort_by === \"last_recalled\") {\n541:     sorted = rows.sort((a, b) => new Date(b.last_recalled_at ?? \"1970\").getTime() - new Date(a.last_recalled_at ?? \"1970\").getTime());\n542:   } else if (input.sort_by === \"recall_count\") {\n543:     sorted = rows.sort((a, b) => (b.recall_count ?? 0) - (a.recall_count ?? 0));\n544:   } else {\n545:     // FTS/semantic path: small result set (≤50), JS sort is O(k log k) — negligible.\n546:     // Use materialised decay_score if available, fall back to computing it.\n547:     sorted = rows\n548:       .map(m => ({ m, score: m.decay_score ?? computeDecayScore(m) }))\n549:       .sort((a, b) => b.score - a.score)\n550:       .map(({ m }) => m);\n551:   }\n552:   if (sorted.length > 0) {\n553:     const placeholders = sorted.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n554:     db.run(\n555:       `UPDATE memories SET last_used_at = datetime('now'), last_recalled_at = datetime('now'),\n556:               recall_count = recall_count + 1,\n557:               first_recalled_at = COALESCE(first_recalled_at, datetime('now'))\n558:        WHERE id IN (${placeholders})`,\n559:       sorted.map(m => m.id),\n560:     );\n561:   }\n562:   const enriched = sorted.map(m => enrichMemory(db, m));\n563:   if (input.includeProvenance) {\n564:     const provMap = listProvenanceBatch(db, enriched.map(m => m.id));\n565:     for (const m of enriched) {\n566:       m.provenance = provMap.get(m.id) ?? [];\n567:     }\n568:   }\n569: \n570:   // Attach explainer (pure function — no extra DB calls).\n571:   if (enriched.length > 0) {\n572:     const { buildExplainer } = await import(\"./recall/explainer.js\");\n573:     for (const m of enriched) {\n574:       m.explainer = buildExplainer({\n575:         importance: m.importance,\n576:         recall_count: m.recall_count ?? 0,\n577:         last_recalled_at: m.last_recalled_at,\n578:         ftsRank: ftsRanks.get(m.id) ?? null,\n579:         semanticScore: semanticScores.get(m.id) ?? null,\n580:       });\n581:     }\n582:   }\n583: \n584:   return enriched;\n585: }\n586: \n587: export function relate(input: {\n588:   source_id: number;\n589:   target_id: number;\n590:   relationship_type: RelationshipType;\n591: }): void {\n592:   const db = getDb();\n593:   if (!db.query<{ id: number }, [number]>(`SELECT id FROM memories WHERE id=?`).get(input.source_id)) {\n594:     throw new Error(`Source memory ${input.source_id} not found`);\n595:   }\n596:   if (!db.query<{ id: number }, [number]>(`SELECT id FROM memories WHERE id=?`).get(input.target_id)) {\n597:     throw new Error(`Target memory ${input.target_id} not found`);\n598:   }\n599:   db.run(\n600:     `INSERT OR IGNORE INTO memory_relations (source_memory_id, target_memory_id, relationship_type)\n601:      VALUES (?, ?, ?)`,\n602:     [input.source_id, input.target_id, input.relationship_type]\n603:   );\n604: }\n605: \n606: export function forget(input: { id: number; reason?: string; skipExport?: boolean; actor?: string; sessionId?: string }): void {\n607:   const db = getDb();\n608:   const snap = snapshotMemory(db, input.id);\n609:   if (!snap) throw new Error(`Memory ${input.id} not found`);\n610:   db.run(`DELETE FROM memories WHERE id=?`, [input.id]);\n611:   tryAudit(() => insertAudit(db, {\n612:     memory_id: input.id,\n613:     op: \"forget\",\n614:     actor: input.actor ?? \"mcp:ltm_forget\",\n615:     session_id: input.sessionId,\n616:     before_json: JSON.stringify(snap),\n617:     after_json: null,\n618:   }));\n619:   if (!input.skipExport) exportMarkdown();\n620: }\n621: \n622: export function getSimilarMemories(\n623:   db: Database,\n624:   queryVec: Float32Array,\n625:   opts: { projectScope?: string; limit?: number; minImportance?: number }\n626: ): Memory[] {\n627:   const { projectScope, limit = 15, minImportance = 2 } = opts;\n628:   const { blobToVec, cosineSimilarity } = require(\"./embeddings.js\") as typeof import(\"./embeddings.js\");\n629: \n630:   let query: string;\n631:   let params: (string | number)[];\n632: \n633:   if (projectScope) {\n634:     query = `SELECT * FROM memories WHERE project_scope=? AND importance>=? AND embedding IS NOT NULL AND status='active' LIMIT ${limit * 3}`;\n635:     params = [projectScope, minImportance];\n636:   } else {\n637:     query = `SELECT * FROM memories WHERE project_scope IS NULL AND importance>=? AND embedding IS NOT NULL AND status='active' LIMIT ${limit * 3}`;\n638:     params = [minImportance];\n639:   }\n640: \n641:   const rows = db.query<Memory & { embedding: Buffer }, typeof params>(query).all(...params);\n642: \n643:   const scored = rows.map(row => {\n644:     const { embedding, ...mem } = row as Memory & { embedding: Buffer };\n645:     const sim = cosineSimilarity(queryVec, blobToVec(embedding));\n646:     return { mem, sim };\n647:   });\n648: \n649:   scored.sort((a, b) => b.sim - a.sim);\n650:   return scored.slice(0, limit).map(s => s.mem);\n651: }\n652: \n653: export function getContextMerge(project: string): { globals: Memory[]; scoped: Memory[] } {\n654:   const db = getDb();\n655:   const sortByDecay = (arr: Memory[]) =>\n656:     arr.map(m => ({ m, score: computeDecayScore(m) }))\n657:        .sort((a, b) => b.score - a.score)\n658:        .map(({ m }) => m);\n659: \n660:   const SLIM = `id, content, category, importance, confidence, source, project_scope, dedup_key,\n661:                created_at, last_confirmed_at, last_used_at, confirm_count, status,\n662:                first_recalled_at, last_recalled_at, recall_count, superseded_by, superseded_at,\n663:                workspace_id, agent_id`;\n664:   const globals = sortByDecay(db.query<Memory, []>(\n665:     `SELECT ${SLIM} FROM memories WHERE importance >= 4 AND project_scope IS NULL AND status = 'active'`\n666:   ).all());\n667: \n668:   const scoped = sortByDecay(db.query<Memory, [string]>(\n669:     `SELECT ${SLIM} FROM memories WHERE project_scope=? AND importance >= 3 AND status = 'active' LIMIT 15`\n670:   ).all(project));\n671: \n672:   const allIds = [...globals, ...scoped].map(m => m.id);\n673:   updateLastUsed(allIds);\n674: \n675:   return { globals, scoped };\n676: }\n\n(Showing lines 417-676 of 780. Use offset=677 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"export async function recall(input: RecallInput = {}): Promise<MemoryWithRelations[]> {\n  const db = getDb();\n  const limit = input.limit ?? 10;\n\n  let ids: Set<number> | null = null;\n  const ftsRanks = new Map<number, number>();      // id → normalized [0,1]\n  const semanticScores = new Map<number, number>(); // id → cosine similarity [0,1]\n\n  if (input.query) {\n    // Sanitize for FTS5: quote each token (prevents reserved-word errors) and join with OR\n    const ftsQuery = input.query\n      .trim()\n      .split(/\\s+/)\n      .filter(Boolean)\n      .map(t => `\"${t.replace(/\"/g, '\"\"')}\"`)\n      .join(\" OR \");\n    const ftsResults = db.query<{ rowid: number; rank: number }, [string]>(\n      `SELECT rowid, rank FROM memories_fts WHERE memories_fts MATCH ? ORDER BY rank LIMIT 50`\n    ).all(ftsQuery);\n    ids = new Set<number>();","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","text":"export async function recall(input: RecallInput = {}): Promise<MemoryWithRelations[]> {\n  const db = getDb();\n  const limit = input.limit ?? 10;\n\n  let ids: Set<number> | null = null;\n  const ftsRanks = new Map<number, number>();      // id → normalized [0,1]\n  const semanticScores = new Map<number, number>(); // id → cosine similarity [0,1]\n\n  if (input.query) {\n    // Sanitize for FTS5: quote each token (prevents reserved-word errors) and join with OR\n    const ftsQuery = input.query\n      .trim()\n      .split(/\\s+/)\n      .filter(Boolean)\n      .map(t => `\"${t.replace(/\"/g, '\"\"')}\"`)\n      .join(\" OR \");\n    const ftsResults = db.query<{ rowid: number; rank: number }, [string]>(\n      `SELECT rowid, rank FROM memories_fts WHERE memories_fts MATCH ? ORDER BY rank LIMIT 50`\n    ).all(ftsQuery);\n    ids = new Set<number>();\n    for (const r of ftsResults) {\n      ids.add(r.rowid);\n      // FTS5 BM25 rank is a negative number (closer to 0 = better).\n      // Math.exp maps it to (0, 1] where 1 is a perfect match.\n      ftsRanks.set(r.rowid, Math.exp(r.rank));\n    }\n\n    // Semantic fallback: if FTS5 returned fewer results than requested, augment with vector search\n    if (ids.size < limit) {\n      const { readConfigSync } = await import(\"./config.js\");\n      const cfg = readConfigSync();\n      const semanticEnabled = cfg.ltm?.semanticFallback !== false; // default true\n      if (semanticEnabled) {\n        try {\n          const { getSimilarMemories } = await import(\"./embeddings.js\");\n          const semantic = await getSimilarMemories(input.query, limit * 2, 0.5);\n          for (const m of semantic) {\n            ids.add(m.id);\n            semanticScores.set(m.id, m.similarity);\n          }\n        } catch (err) {\n          process.stderr.write(`[recall] Semantic fallback failed: ${err}\\n`);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (input.tags && input.tags.length > 0) {\n    const tagIds = input.tags.map(t => {\n      const row = db.query<{ id: number }, [string]>(`SELECT id FROM tags WHERE name=?`).get(t.toLowerCase());\n      return row?.id;\n    }).filter((id): id is number => id !== undefined);\n\n    if (tagIds.length > 0) {\n      const placeholders = tagIds.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n      const tagMemIds = db.query<{ memory_id: number }, number[]>(\n        `SELECT DISTINCT memory_id FROM memory_tags WHERE tag_id IN (${placeholders})`\n      ).all(...tagIds).map(r => r.memory_id);\n\n      const tagSet = new Set(tagMemIds);\n      ids = ids ? new Set([...ids].filter(id => tagSet.has(id))) : tagSet;\n    }\n  }\n\n  const conditions: string[] = [];\n  const params: (string | number | null)[] = [];\n\n  if (ids !== null) {\n    if (ids.size === 0) return [];\n    const placeholders = [...ids].map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n    conditions.push(`id IN (${placeholders})`);\n    params.push(...ids);\n  }\n\n  if (input.category) {\n    conditions.push(\"category=?\");\n    params.push(input.category);\n  }\n\n  if (input.project) {\n    conditions.push(\"(project_scope IS NULL OR project_scope=?)\");\n    params.push(input.project);\n  }\n\n  if (input.workspace_id) {\n    conditions.push(\"(workspace_id IS NULL OR workspace_id=?)\");\n    params.push(input.workspace_id);\n  }\n  if (input.agent_id) {\n    conditions.push(\"(agent_id IS NULL OR agent_id=?)\");\n    params.push(input.agent_id);\n  }\n\n  conditions.push(\"status = 'active'\");\n\n  if (input.since) {\n    conditions.push(\"(created_at > ? OR last_recalled_at > ?)\");\n    params.push(input.since, input.since);\n  }\n  if (input.until) {\n    conditions.push(\"(created_at < ? OR last_recalled_at < ?)\");\n    params.push(input.until, input.until);\n  }\n\n  const where = `WHERE ${conditions.join(\" AND \")}`;\n  // Explicit columns — excludes embedding blob (~260 KB/row) from hot recall path.\n  // Use getById(id, { withEmbedding: true }) when the blob is needed.\n  // default sort (no query): ORDER BY decay_score DESC pushed to SQL → O(log N)\n  const defaultSqlSort = (!input.sort_by || input.sort_by === \"relevance\") && ids === null;\n  const orderBy = defaultSqlSort ? \"ORDER BY decay_score DESC\" : \"\";\n  const rows = db.query<Memory, typeof params>(\n    `SELECT id, content, category, importance, confidence, source, project_scope, dedup_key,\n            created_at, last_confirmed_at, last_used_at, confirm_count, status,\n            first_recalled_at, last_recalled_at, recall_count, superseded_by, superseded_at,\n            workspace_id, agent_id, decay_score\n     FROM memories ${where} ${orderBy} LIMIT ${limit}`\n  ).all(...params);\n\n  let sorted: typeof rows;\n  if (defaultSqlSort) {\n    sorted = rows; // already ordered by decay_score DESC in SQL\n  } else if (input.sort_by === \"created\") {\n    sorted = rows.sort((a, b) => new Date(b.created_at).getTime() - new Date(a.created_at).getTime());\n  } else if (input.sort_by === \"last_recalled\") {\n    sorted = rows.sort((a, b) => new Date(b.last_recalled_at ?? \"1970\").getTime() - new Date(a.last_recalled_at ?? \"1970\").getTime());\n  } else if (input.sort_by === \"recall_count\") {\n    sorted = rows.sort((a, b) => (b.recall_count ?? 0) - (a.recall_count ?? 0));\n  } else {\n    // FTS/semantic path: small result set (≤50), JS sort is O(k log k) — negligible.\n    // Use materialised decay_score if available, fall back to computing it.\n    sorted = rows\n      .map(m => ({ m, score: m.decay_score ?? computeDecayScore(m) }))\n      .sort((a, b) => b.score - a.score)\n      .map(({ m }) => m);\n  }\n  if (sorted.length > 0) {\n    const placeholders = sorted.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n    db.run(\n      `UPDATE memories SET last_used_at = datetime('now'), last_recalled_at = datetime('now'),\n              recall_count = recall_count + 1,\n              first_recalled_at = COALESCE(first_recalled_at, datetime('now'))\n       WHERE id IN (${placeholders})`,\n      sorted.map(m => m.id),\n    );\n  }\n  const enriched = sorted.map(m => enrichMemory(db, m));\n  if (input.includeProvenance) {\n    const provMap = listProvenanceBatch(db, enriched.map(m => m.id));\n    for (const m of enriched) {\n      m.provenance = provMap.get(m.id) ?? [];\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Attach explainer (pure function — no extra DB calls).\n  if (enriched.length > 0) {\n    const { buildExplainer } = await import(\"./recall/explainer.js\");\n    for (const m of enriched) {\n      m.explainer = buildExplainer({\n        importance: m.importance,\n        recall_count: m.recall_count ?? 0,\n        last_recalled_at: m.last_recalled_at,\n        ftsRank: ftsRanks.get(m.id) ?? null,\n        semanticScore: semanticScores.get(m.id) ?? null,\n      });\n    }\n  }\n\n  return enriched;\n}\n\nexport function relate(input: {\n  source_id: number;\n  target_id: number;\n  relationship_type: RelationshipType;\n}): void {\n  const db = getDb();\n  if (!db.query<{ id: number }, [number]>(`SELECT id FROM memories WHERE id=?`).get(input.source_id)) {\n    throw new Error(`Source memory ${input.source_id} not found`);\n  }\n  if (!db.query<{ id: number }, [number]>(`SELECT id FROM memories WHERE id=?`).get(input.target_id)) {\n    throw new Error(`Target memory ${input.target_id} not found`);\n  }\n  db.run(\n    `INSERT OR IGNORE INTO memory_relations (source_memory_id, target_memory_id, relationship_type)\n     VALUES (?, ?, ?)`,\n    [input.source_id, input.target_id, input.relationship_type]\n  );\n}\n\nexport function forget(input: { id: number; reason?: string; skipExport?: boolean; actor?: string; sessionId?: string }): void {\n  const db = getDb();\n  const snap = snapshotMemory(db, input.id);\n  if (!snap) throw new Error(`Memory ${input.id} not found`);\n  db.run(`DELETE FROM memories WHERE id=?`, [input.id]);\n  tryAudit(() => insertAudit(db, {\n    memory_id: input.id,\n    op: \"forget\",\n    actor: input.actor ?? \"mcp:ltm_forget\",\n    session_id: input.sessionId,\n    before_json: JSON.stringify(snap),\n    after_json: null,\n  }));\n  if (!input.skipExport) exportMarkdown();\n}\n\nexport function getSimilarMemories(\n  db: Database,\n  queryVec: Float32Array,\n  opts: { projectScope?: string; limit?: number; minImportance?: number }\n): Memory[] {\n  const { projectScope, limit = 15, minImportance = 2 } = opts;\n  const { blobToVec, cosineSimilarity } = require(\"./embeddings.js\") as typeof import(\"./embeddings.js\");\n\n  let query: string;\n  let params: (string | number)[];\n\n  if (projectScope) {\n    query = `SELECT * FROM memories WHERE project_scope=? AND importance>=? AND embedding IS NOT NULL AND status='active' LIMIT ${limit * 3}`;\n    params = [projectScope, minImportance];\n  } else {\n    query = `SELECT * FROM memories WHERE project_scope IS NULL AND importance>=? AND embedding IS NOT NULL AND status='active' LIMIT ${limit * 3}`;\n    params = [minImportance];\n  }\n\n  const rows = db.query<Memory & { embedding: Buffer }, typeof params>(query).all(...params);\n\n  const scored = rows.map(row => {\n    const { embedding, ...mem } = row as Memory & { embedding: Buffer };\n    const sim = cosineSimilarity(queryVec, blobToVec(embedding));\n    return { mem, sim };\n  });\n\n  scored.sort((a, b) => b.sim - a.sim);\n  return scored.slice(0, limit).map(s => s.mem);\n}\n\nexport function getContextMerge(project: string): { globals: Memory[]; scoped: Memory[] } {\n  const db = getDb();\n  const sortByDecay = (arr: Memory[]) =>\n    arr.map(m => ({ m, score: computeDecayScore(m) }))\n       .sort((a, b) => b.score - a.score)\n       .map(({ m }) => m);\n\n  const SLIM = `id, content, category, importance, confidence, source, project_scope, dedup_key,\n               created_at, last_confirmed_at, last_used_at, confirm_count, status,\n               first_recalled_at, last_recalled_at, recall_count, superseded_by, superseded_at,\n               workspace_id, agent_id`;\n  const globals = sortByDecay(db.query<Memory, []>(\n    `SELECT ${SLIM} FROM memories WHERE importance >= 4 AND project_scope IS NULL AND status = 'active'`\n  ).all());\n\n  const scoped = sortByDecay(db.query<Memory, [string]>(\n    `SELECT ${SLIM} FROM memories WHERE project_scope=? AND importance >= 3 AND status = 'active' LIMIT 15`\n  ).all(project));\n\n  const allIds = [...globals, ...scoped].map(m => m.id);\n  updateLastUsed(allIds);\n\n  return { globals, scoped };\n}","lineStart":417,"lineEnd":676,"totalLines":780,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","time":{"start":1780924926109,"end":1780924926151}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c5a652d3b65a9a9016a26c1fe0b7c819190edf80a0fc0b3d3"}},"id":"prt_ea765c898001bOD8tS3Hfvp2eL","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","messageID":"msg_ea765964c0018NPwXaY45vNhEv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780924926159,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ewQCwyU2F9WFMfafH0gSowPb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/recall/categorise.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/recall/categorise.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /**\n2:  * recall/categorise.ts — Heuristic + LLM-fallback category classifier.\n3:  *\n4:  * Strategy:\n5:  *   1. Score each MemoryCategory by keyword density in the content.\n6:  *   2. If the top score meets or exceeds confidenceThreshold → return it.\n7:  *   3. Otherwise call Anthropic Messages API (claude-haiku) to classify.\n8:  *   4. If LLM call fails, fall back to the best heuristic guess.\n9:  */\n10: \n11: import type { MemoryCategory } from \"../dao/types.js\";\n12: \n13: export interface CategoriseResult {\n14:   category: MemoryCategory;\n15:   confidence: number;\n16:   source: \"heuristic\" | \"llm\";\n17: }\n18: \n19: // ── Keyword tables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: \n21: const KEYWORDS: Record<MemoryCategory, string[]> = {\n22:   preference: [\n23:     \"prefer\", \"always use\", \"convention\", \"style\", \"format\", \"naming\",\n24:     \"use .* not\", \"default\", \"standard\", \"i like\", \"we use\",\n25:   ],\n26:   architecture: [\n27:     \"architecture\", \"design\", \"structure\", \"system\", \"component\", \"module\",\n28:     \"layer\", \"schema\", \"database\", \"api\", \"interface\", \"integration\",\n29:     \"dependency\", \"abstraction\", \"service\",\n30:   ],\n31:   gotcha: [\n32:     \"warning\", \"pitfall\", \"bug\", \"avoid\", \"never\", \"don't\", \"dont\",\n33:     \"broken\", \"fail\", \"trap\", \"careful\", \"watch out\", \"⚠\", \"issue\",\n34:     \"error\", \"problem\", \"beware\",\n35:   ],\n36:   pattern: [\n37:     \"pattern\", \"approach\", \"recipe\", \"template\", \"boilerplate\",\n38:     \"solution\", \"technique\", \"method\", \"strategy\", \"implement\",\n39:     \"how to\", \"example\", \"reusable\",\n40:   ],\n41:   workflow: [\n42:     \"process\", \"step\", \"procedure\", \"workflow\", \"pipeline\",\n43:     \"sequence\", \"flow\", \"first\", \"then\", \"finally\", \"checklist\",\n44:     \"before\", \"after\", \"when to\",\n45:   ],\n46:   constraint: [\n47:     \"must\", \"required\", \"mandatory\", \"cannot\", \"should not\",\n48:     \"limit\", \"restriction\", \"enforce\", \"rule\", \"policy\", \"compliance\",\n49:     \"always\", \"never allowed\", \"forbidden\",\n50:   ],\n51: };\n52: \n53: // ── Heuristic scorer ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n54: \n55: function scoreHeuristic(content: string): { category: MemoryCategory; confidence: number } {\n56:   const lower = content.toLowerCase();\n57: \n58:   const scores = Object.entries(KEYWORDS).map(([cat, keywords]) => {\n59:     let hits = 0;\n60:     for (const kw of keywords) {\n61:       const re = new RegExp(kw, \"gi\");\n62:       const matches = lower.match(re);\n63:       if (matches) hits += matches.length;\n64:     }\n65:     return { category: cat as MemoryCategory, hits };\n66:   });\n67: \n68:   const total = scores.reduce((s, x) => s + x.hits, 0);\n69:   const best = scores.sort((a, b) => b.hits - a.hits)[0];\n70: \n71:   if (!best || best.hits === 0) {\n72:     return { category: \"pattern\", confidence: 0 };\n73:   }\n74: \n75:   // Confidence = share of total hits, clamped to [0, 1].\n76:   // A dominant category scores high; if two categories are equal, confidence halves.\n77:   const confidence = Math.min(best.hits / Math.max(total, 1), 1);\n78:   return { category: best.category, confidence };\n79: }\n80: \n81: // ── LLM fallback ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n82: \n83: const CATEGORIES_LIST = Object.keys(KEYWORDS).join(\", \");\n84: const VALID_CATEGORIES = new Set<string>(Object.keys(KEYWORDS));\n85: \n86: async function classifyWithLlm(content: string): Promise<MemoryCategory | null> {\n87:   const apiKey = process.env[\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"];\n88:   if (!apiKey) return null;\n89: \n90:   try {\n91:     const res = await fetch(\"https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages\", {\n92:       method: \"POST\",\n93:       headers: {\n94:         \"x-api-key\": apiKey,\n95:         \"anthropic-version\": \"2023-06-01\",\n96:         \"content-type\": \"application/json\",\n97:       },\n98:       body: JSON.stringify({\n99:         model: \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n100:         max_tokens: 20,\n101:         messages: [{\n102:           role: \"user\",\n103:           content: `Classify this memory into exactly one category. Reply with only the category name, nothing else.\\n\\nCategories: ${CATEGORIES_LIST}\\n\\nMemory: ${content.slice(0, 500)}`,\n104:         }],\n105:       }),\n106:       signal: AbortSignal.timeout(8_000),\n107:     });\n108: \n109:     if (!res.ok) return null;\n110: \n111:     const json = await res.json() as { content?: Array<{ type: string; text?: string }> };\n112:     const text = json.content?.[0]?.text?.trim().toLowerCase() ?? \"\";\n113: \n114:     return VALID_CATEGORIES.has(text) ? (text as MemoryCategory) : null;\n115:   } catch {\n116:     return null;\n117:   }\n118: }\n119: \n120: // ── Public API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n121: \n122: export async function categorise(\n123:   content: string,\n124:   confidenceThreshold = 0.6,\n125: ): Promise<CategoriseResult> {\n126:   const heuristic = scoreHeuristic(content);\n127: \n128:   if (heuristic.confidence >= confidenceThreshold) {\n129:     return { ...heuristic, source: \"heuristic\" };\n130:   }\n131: \n132:   const llmCategory = await classifyWithLlm(content);\n133:   if (llmCategory) {\n134:     return { category: llmCategory, confidence: 1.0, source: \"llm\" };\n135:   }\n136: \n137:   // LLM unavailable or failed — return best heuristic guess regardless of confidence\n138:   return { ...heuristic, source: \"heuristic\" };\n139: }\n\n(End of file - total 139 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * recall/categorise.ts — Heuristic + LLM-fallback category classifier.\n *\n * Strategy:\n *   1. Score each MemoryCategory by keyword density in the content.\n *   2. If the top score meets or exceeds confidenceThreshold → return it.\n *   3. Otherwise call Anthropic Messages API (claude-haiku) to classify.\n *   4. If LLM call fails, fall back to the best heuristic guess.\n */\n\nimport type { MemoryCategory } from \"../dao/types.js\";\n\nexport interface CategoriseResult {\n  category: MemoryCategory;\n  confidence: number;\n  source: \"heuristic\" | \"llm\";\n}\n\n// ── Keyword tables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/recall/categorise.ts","text":"/**\n * recall/categorise.ts — Heuristic + LLM-fallback category classifier.\n *\n * Strategy:\n *   1. Score each MemoryCategory by keyword density in the content.\n *   2. If the top score meets or exceeds confidenceThreshold → return it.\n *   3. Otherwise call Anthropic Messages API (claude-haiku) to classify.\n *   4. If LLM call fails, fall back to the best heuristic guess.\n */\n\nimport type { MemoryCategory } from \"../dao/types.js\";\n\nexport interface CategoriseResult {\n  category: MemoryCategory;\n  confidence: number;\n  source: \"heuristic\" | \"llm\";\n}\n\n// ── Keyword tables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst KEYWORDS: Record<MemoryCategory, string[]> = {\n  preference: [\n    \"prefer\", \"always use\", \"convention\", \"style\", \"format\", \"naming\",\n    \"use .* not\", \"default\", \"standard\", \"i like\", \"we use\",\n  ],\n  architecture: [\n    \"architecture\", \"design\", \"structure\", \"system\", \"component\", \"module\",\n    \"layer\", \"schema\", \"database\", \"api\", \"interface\", \"integration\",\n    \"dependency\", \"abstraction\", \"service\",\n  ],\n  gotcha: [\n    \"warning\", \"pitfall\", \"bug\", \"avoid\", \"never\", \"don't\", \"dont\",\n    \"broken\", \"fail\", \"trap\", \"careful\", \"watch out\", \"⚠\", \"issue\",\n    \"error\", \"problem\", \"beware\",\n  ],\n  pattern: [\n    \"pattern\", \"approach\", \"recipe\", \"template\", \"boilerplate\",\n    \"solution\", \"technique\", \"method\", \"strategy\", \"implement\",\n    \"how to\", \"example\", \"reusable\",\n  ],\n  workflow: [\n    \"process\", \"step\", \"procedure\", \"workflow\", \"pipeline\",\n    \"sequence\", \"flow\", \"first\", \"then\", \"finally\", \"checklist\",\n    \"before\", \"after\", \"when to\",\n  ],\n  constraint: [\n    \"must\", \"required\", \"mandatory\", \"cannot\", \"should not\",\n    \"limit\", \"restriction\", \"enforce\", \"rule\", \"policy\", \"compliance\",\n    \"always\", \"never allowed\", \"forbidden\",\n  ],\n};\n\n// ── Heuristic scorer ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction scoreHeuristic(content: string): { category: MemoryCategory; confidence: number } {\n  const lower = content.toLowerCase();\n\n  const scores = Object.entries(KEYWORDS).map(([cat, keywords]) => {\n    let hits = 0;\n    for (const kw of keywords) {\n      const re = new RegExp(kw, \"gi\");\n      const matches = lower.match(re);\n      if (matches) hits += matches.length;\n    }\n    return { category: cat as MemoryCategory, hits };\n  });\n\n  const total = scores.reduce((s, x) => s + x.hits, 0);\n  const best = scores.sort((a, b) => b.hits - a.hits)[0];\n\n  if (!best || best.hits === 0) {\n    return { category: \"pattern\", confidence: 0 };\n  }\n\n  // Confidence = share of total hits, clamped to [0, 1].\n  // A dominant category scores high; if two categories are equal, confidence halves.\n  const confidence = Math.min(best.hits / Math.max(total, 1), 1);\n  return { category: best.category, confidence };\n}\n\n// ── LLM fallback ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst CATEGORIES_LIST = Object.keys(KEYWORDS).join(\", \");\nconst VALID_CATEGORIES = new Set<string>(Object.keys(KEYWORDS));\n\nasync function classifyWithLlm(content: string): Promise<MemoryCategory | null> {\n  const apiKey = process.env[\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"];\n  if (!apiKey) return null;\n\n  try {\n    const res = await fetch(\"https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages\", {\n      method: \"POST\",\n      headers: {\n        \"x-api-key\": apiKey,\n        \"anthropic-version\": \"2023-06-01\",\n        \"content-type\": \"application/json\",\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        model: \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens: 20,\n        messages: [{\n          role: \"user\",\n          content: `Classify this memory into exactly one category. Reply with only the category name, nothing else.\\n\\nCategories: ${CATEGORIES_LIST}\\n\\nMemory: ${content.slice(0, 500)}`,\n        }],\n      }),\n      signal: AbortSignal.timeout(8_000),\n    });\n\n    if (!res.ok) return null;\n\n    const json = await res.json() as { content?: Array<{ type: string; text?: string }> };\n    const text = json.content?.[0]?.text?.trim().toLowerCase() ?? \"\";\n\n    return VALID_CATEGORIES.has(text) ? (text as MemoryCategory) : null;\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\n// ── Public API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport async function categorise(\n  content: string,\n  confidenceThreshold = 0.6,\n): Promise<CategoriseResult> {\n  const heuristic = scoreHeuristic(content);\n\n  if (heuristic.confidence >= confidenceThreshold) {\n    return { ...heuristic, source: \"heuristic\" };\n  }\n\n  const llmCategory = await classifyWithLlm(content);\n  if (llmCategory) {\n    return { category: llmCategory, confidence: 1.0, source: \"llm\" };\n  }\n\n  // LLM unavailable or failed — return best heuristic guess regardless of confidence\n  return { ...heuristic, source: \"heuristic\" };\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":139,"totalLines":139,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/recall/categorise.ts","time":{"start":1780924926115,"end":1780924926156}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c5a652d3b65a9a9016a26c1fe0b908191be7e7ddec652c416"}},"id":"prt_ea765c8a100152oo05ULrtx0y6","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","messageID":"msg_ea765964c0018NPwXaY45vNhEv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780924926169,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_D8Lxu30VIrzqMXRE0N0f8tN6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/recall/explainer.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/recall/explainer.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /**\n2:  * recall/explainer.ts — Pure function that builds a score breakdown for each recall result.\n3:  * No DB access. No side effects. Deterministic.\n4:  *\n5:  * Score formula:\n6:  *   totalScore = (fts * 0.40) + (semantic * 0.35) + (importance * 0.15) + (recency * 0.10)\n7:  *   When provider is disabled, FTS weight absorbs the semantic slot:\n8:  *   totalScore = (fts * 0.75) + (importance * 0.15) + (recency * 0.10)\n9:  */\n10: \n11: export type MemoryTemperature = \"hot\" | \"warm\" | \"cool\" | \"cold\";\n12: \n13: export interface RecallExplainer {\n14:   ftsRank: number | null;\n15:   semanticScore: number | null;\n16:   importanceBoost: number;\n17:   recencyBoost: number;\n18:   totalScore: number;\n19:   temperature: MemoryTemperature;\n20: }\n21: \n22: export interface ExplainerInput {\n23:   importance: number;\n24:   recall_count: number;\n25:   last_recalled_at: string | null | undefined;\n26:   ftsRank?: number | null;\n27:   semanticScore?: number | null;\n28: }\n29: \n30: /** Compute memory temperature from access pattern. */\n31: export function computeTemperature(\n32:   recallCount: number,\n33:   lastRecalledAt: string | null | undefined,\n34: ): MemoryTemperature {\n35:   const daysSince = lastRecalledAt\n36:     ? (Date.now() - new Date(lastRecalledAt).getTime()) / 86_400_000\n37:     : Infinity;\n38: \n39:   if (recallCount >= 10 || daysSince <= 7) return \"hot\";\n40:   if (recallCount >= 3 || daysSince <= 30) return \"warm\";\n41:   if (recallCount >= 1 || daysSince <= 90) return \"cool\";\n42:   return \"cold\";\n43: }\n44: \n45: /** Build a RecallExplainer for a single memory result. Pure function — no I/O. */\n46: export function buildExplainer(input: ExplainerInput): RecallExplainer {\n47:   const importanceBoost = Math.min(input.importance, 5) / 5;\n48: \n49:   const daysSince = input.last_recalled_at\n50:     ? (Date.now() - new Date(input.last_recalled_at).getTime()) / 86_400_000\n51:     : 90;\n52:   const recencyBoost = Math.max(0, 1 - daysSince / 90);\n53: \n54:   const ftsRank = input.ftsRank ?? null;\n55:   const semanticScore = input.semanticScore ?? null;\n56: \n57:   let totalScore: number;\n58:   if (semanticScore !== null && ftsRank !== null) {\n59:     totalScore = (ftsRank * 0.40) + (semanticScore * 0.35) + (importanceBoost * 0.15) + (recencyBoost * 0.10);\n60:   } else if (ftsRank !== null) {\n61:     totalScore = (ftsRank * 0.75) + (importanceBoost * 0.15) + (recencyBoost * 0.10);\n62:   } else if (semanticScore !== null) {\n63:     totalScore = (semanticScore * 0.75) + (importanceBoost * 0.15) + (recencyBoost * 0.10);\n64:   } else {\n65:     totalScore = (importanceBoost * 0.15) + (recencyBoost * 0.10);\n66:   }\n67: \n68:   return {\n69:     ftsRank,\n70:     semanticScore,\n71:     importanceBoost,\n72:     recencyBoost,\n73:     totalScore,\n74:     temperature: computeTemperature(input.recall_count, input.last_recalled_at),\n75:   };\n76: }\n\n(End of file - total 76 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * recall/explainer.ts — Pure function that builds a score breakdown for each recall result.\n * No DB access. No side effects. Deterministic.\n *\n * Score formula:\n *   totalScore = (fts * 0.40) + (semantic * 0.35) + (importance * 0.15) + (recency * 0.10)\n *   When provider is disabled, FTS weight absorbs the semantic slot:\n *   totalScore = (fts * 0.75) + (importance * 0.15) + (recency * 0.10)\n */\n\nexport type MemoryTemperature = \"hot\" | \"warm\" | \"cool\" | \"cold\";\n\nexport interface RecallExplainer {\n  ftsRank: number | null;\n  semanticScore: number | null;\n  importanceBoost: number;\n  recencyBoost: number;\n  totalScore: number;\n  temperature: MemoryTemperature;\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/recall/explainer.ts","text":"/**\n * recall/explainer.ts — Pure function that builds a score breakdown for each recall result.\n * No DB access. No side effects. Deterministic.\n *\n * Score formula:\n *   totalScore = (fts * 0.40) + (semantic * 0.35) + (importance * 0.15) + (recency * 0.10)\n *   When provider is disabled, FTS weight absorbs the semantic slot:\n *   totalScore = (fts * 0.75) + (importance * 0.15) + (recency * 0.10)\n */\n\nexport type MemoryTemperature = \"hot\" | \"warm\" | \"cool\" | \"cold\";\n\nexport interface RecallExplainer {\n  ftsRank: number | null;\n  semanticScore: number | null;\n  importanceBoost: number;\n  recencyBoost: number;\n  totalScore: number;\n  temperature: MemoryTemperature;\n}\n\nexport interface ExplainerInput {\n  importance: number;\n  recall_count: number;\n  last_recalled_at: string | null | undefined;\n  ftsRank?: number | null;\n  semanticScore?: number | null;\n}\n\n/** Compute memory temperature from access pattern. */\nexport function computeTemperature(\n  recallCount: number,\n  lastRecalledAt: string | null | undefined,\n): MemoryTemperature {\n  const daysSince = lastRecalledAt\n    ? (Date.now() - new Date(lastRecalledAt).getTime()) / 86_400_000\n    : Infinity;\n\n  if (recallCount >= 10 || daysSince <= 7) return \"hot\";\n  if (recallCount >= 3 || daysSince <= 30) return \"warm\";\n  if (recallCount >= 1 || daysSince <= 90) return \"cool\";\n  return \"cold\";\n}\n\n/** Build a RecallExplainer for a single memory result. Pure function — no I/O. */\nexport function buildExplainer(input: ExplainerInput): RecallExplainer {\n  const importanceBoost = Math.min(input.importance, 5) / 5;\n\n  const daysSince = input.last_recalled_at\n    ? (Date.now() - new Date(input.last_recalled_at).getTime()) / 86_400_000\n    : 90;\n  const recencyBoost = Math.max(0, 1 - daysSince / 90);\n\n  const ftsRank = input.ftsRank ?? null;\n  const semanticScore = input.semanticScore ?? null;\n\n  let totalScore: number;\n  if (semanticScore !== null && ftsRank !== null) {\n    totalScore = (ftsRank * 0.40) + (semanticScore * 0.35) + (importanceBoost * 0.15) + (recencyBoost * 0.10);\n  } else if (ftsRank !== null) {\n    totalScore = (ftsRank * 0.75) + (importanceBoost * 0.15) + (recencyBoost * 0.10);\n  } else if (semanticScore !== null) {\n    totalScore = (semanticScore * 0.75) + (importanceBoost * 0.15) + (recencyBoost * 0.10);\n  } else {\n    totalScore = (importanceBoost * 0.15) + (recencyBoost * 0.10);\n  }\n\n  return {\n    ftsRank,\n    semanticScore,\n    importanceBoost,\n    recencyBoost,\n    totalScore,\n    temperature: computeTemperature(input.recall_count, input.last_recalled_at),\n  };\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":76,"totalLines":76,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/recall/explainer.ts","time":{"start":1780924926112,"end":1780924926166}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c5a652d3b65a9a9016a26c1fe0b888191b18245663ac712e3"}},"id":"prt_ea765c89e001ZycEm5rAchcqrD","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","messageID":"msg_ea765964c0018NPwXaY45vNhEv"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780924926613,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"id":"prt_ea765ca8e001LXrk2f7jtFuUR5","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"a9fc294ba33bd7ccd02b5e458f1802a9133aa1ba","messageID":"msg_ea765964c0018NPwXaY45vNhEv","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":47802,"input":4279,"output":426,"reasoning":89,"cache":{"write":0,"read":43008}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780924928878,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"id":"prt_ea765d36d001SgxENCnCLl9ZCY","messageID":"msg_ea765cc190019agoUNAu6yQRpq","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","snapshot":"b83adbca5b60990667b12eaeafe8616957b85d25","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780924936285,"sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_AOyfs6CuefbeVZDXwtpgujp5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","offset":200,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n200: /** Half-life in days by importance level. Infinity = never decays. */\n201: const HALF_LIVES: Record<number, number> = {\n202:   5: Infinity,\n203:   4: 180,\n204:   3: 90,\n205:   2: 30,\n206:   1: 14,\n207: };\n208: \n209: /** Memories below this score are soft-deprecated (not deleted). */\n210: const DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD = 0.25;\n211: \n212: /**\n213:  * Compute effective relevance score.\n214:  * score = importance × confidence × decay\n215:  * decay = 0.5 ^ (days_since / half_life)  (1.0 for importance=5)\n216:  */\n217: export function computeDecayScore(memory: Memory): number {\n218:   const halfLife = HALF_LIVES[memory.importance] ?? 90;\n219:   if (halfLife === Infinity) {\n220:     return memory.importance * memory.confidence;\n221:   }\n222:   const latestTs = [memory.last_used_at, memory.last_confirmed_at, memory.created_at]\n223:     .map(t => new Date(t).getTime())\n224:     .reduce((a, b) => Math.max(a, b), 0);\n225:   const daysSince = (Date.now() - latestTs) / 86_400_000;\n226:   const decay = Math.pow(0.5, daysSince / halfLife);\n227:   return memory.importance * memory.confidence * decay;\n228: }\n229: \n230: /** Update last_used_at for a batch of memory IDs. */\n231: export function updateLastUsed(ids: number[]): void {\n232:   if (ids.length === 0) return;\n233:   const db = getDb();\n234:   const placeholders = ids.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n235:   db.run(\n236:     `UPDATE memories SET last_used_at = datetime('now') WHERE id IN (${placeholders})`,\n237:     ids\n238:   );\n239: }\n240: \n241: export interface DecayResult {\n242:   deprecated: number;\n243:   scored: number;\n244: }\n245: \n246: /**\n247:  * Compute decay scores for all active memories. Deprecate those below threshold.\n248:  * Protection: importance=5 OR confirm_count>=5 are never deprecated.\n249:  */\n250: export function decayMemories(): DecayResult {\n251:   const db = getDb();\n252: \n253:   const rows = db.query<Memory, []>(\n254:     `SELECT * FROM memories WHERE status = 'active'`\n255:   ).all();\n256: \n257:   const toDeprecate = rows\n258:     .filter(mem => mem.importance !== 5 && mem.confirm_count < 5)\n259:     .filter(mem => computeDecayScore(mem) < DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD)\n260:     .map(mem => mem.id);\n261: \n262:   if (toDeprecate.length > 0) {\n263:     const placeholders = toDeprecate.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n264:     db.run(\n265:       `UPDATE memories SET status = 'deprecated' WHERE id IN (${placeholders})`,\n266:       toDeprecate\n267:     );\n268:   }\n269: \n270:   return { deprecated: toDeprecate.length, scored: rows.length };\n271: }\n272: \n273: // Auto-relation detection — called fire-and-forget from learn()\n274: async function autoDetectRelations(\n275:   newId: number,\n276:   content: string,\n277:   getSimilarMemories: (text: string, topN: number, threshold: number) => Promise<Array<{ id: number; content: string; similarity: number }>>,\n278:   classifyRelation: (a: string, b: string) => Promise<RelationshipType | null>,\n279: ): Promise<void> {\n280:   try {\n281:     const { readConfigSync } = await import(\"./config.js\");\n282:     if (readConfigSync().ltm?.autoRelate === false) return;\n283: \n284:     const candidates = await getSimilarMemories(content, 5, 0.6);\n285:     const others = candidates.filter(c => c.id !== newId);\n286:     if (!others.length) return;\n287: \n288:     await Promise.allSettled(\n289:       others.map(async (candidate) => {\n290:         const relType = await classifyRelation(content, candidate.content);\n291:         if (!relType) return;\n292:         try {\n293:           relate({ source_id: newId, target_id: candidate.id, relationship_type: relType });\n294:         } catch {\n295:           // Memory may have been deleted between detection and insertion — ignore\n296:         }\n297:       })\n298:     );\n299:   } catch (err) {\n300:     process.stderr.write(`[autoDetectRelations] error for memory ${newId}: ${err}\\n`);\n301:   }\n302: }\n303: \n304: export function learn(input: LearnInput): LearnResult {\n305:   const db = getDb();\n306: \n307:   // Scrub secrets before any DB write or dedup check\n308:   const { scrubbed, redactions } = scrubSecrets(input.content);\n309:   if (redactions.length > 0) {\n310:     process.stderr.write(`[learn] Scrubbed ${redactions.length} secret(s): ${redactions.join(\", \")}\\n`);\n311:   }\n312:   const content = scrubbed;\n313: \n314:   const dedupKey = normalizeKey(content);\n315:   const skipExport = input.skipExport ?? false;\n316: \n317:   const existing = db.query<Memory, [string]>(`SELECT * FROM memories WHERE dedup_key=?`).get(dedupKey);\n318: \n319:   const actor = input.actor ?? \"mcp:ltm_learn\";\n\n(Showing lines 200-319 of 780. Use offset=320 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/** Half-life in days by importance level. Infinity = never decays. */\nconst HALF_LIVES: Record<number, number> = {\n  5: Infinity,\n  4: 180,\n  3: 90,\n  2: 30,\n  1: 14,\n};\n\n/** Memories below this score are soft-deprecated (not deleted). */\nconst DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD = 0.25;\n\n/**\n * Compute effective relevance score.\n * score = importance × confidence × decay\n * decay = 0.5 ^ (days_since / half_life)  (1.0 for importance=5)\n */\nexport function computeDecayScore(memory: Memory): number {\n  const halfLife = HALF_LIVES[memory.importance] ?? 90;\n  if (halfLife === Infinity) {","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","text":"/** Half-life in days by importance level. Infinity = never decays. */\nconst HALF_LIVES: Record<number, number> = {\n  5: Infinity,\n  4: 180,\n  3: 90,\n  2: 30,\n  1: 14,\n};\n\n/** Memories below this score are soft-deprecated (not deleted). */\nconst DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD = 0.25;\n\n/**\n * Compute effective relevance score.\n * score = importance × confidence × decay\n * decay = 0.5 ^ (days_since / half_life)  (1.0 for importance=5)\n */\nexport function computeDecayScore(memory: Memory): number {\n  const halfLife = HALF_LIVES[memory.importance] ?? 90;\n  if (halfLife === Infinity) {\n    return memory.importance * memory.confidence;\n  }\n  const latestTs = [memory.last_used_at, memory.last_confirmed_at, memory.created_at]\n    .map(t => new Date(t).getTime())\n    .reduce((a, b) => Math.max(a, b), 0);\n  const daysSince = (Date.now() - latestTs) / 86_400_000;\n  const decay = Math.pow(0.5, daysSince / halfLife);\n  return memory.importance * memory.confidence * decay;\n}\n\n/** Update last_used_at for a batch of memory IDs. */\nexport function updateLastUsed(ids: number[]): void {\n  if (ids.length === 0) return;\n  const db = getDb();\n  const placeholders = ids.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n  db.run(\n    `UPDATE memories SET last_used_at = datetime('now') WHERE id IN (${placeholders})`,\n    ids\n  );\n}\n\nexport interface DecayResult {\n  deprecated: number;\n  scored: number;\n}\n\n/**\n * Compute decay scores for all active memories. Deprecate those below threshold.\n * Protection: importance=5 OR confirm_count>=5 are never deprecated.\n */\nexport function decayMemories(): DecayResult {\n  const db = getDb();\n\n  const rows = db.query<Memory, []>(\n    `SELECT * FROM memories WHERE status = 'active'`\n  ).all();\n\n  const toDeprecate = rows\n    .filter(mem => mem.importance !== 5 && mem.confirm_count < 5)\n    .filter(mem => computeDecayScore(mem) < DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD)\n    .map(mem => mem.id);\n\n  if (toDeprecate.length > 0) {\n    const placeholders = toDeprecate.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n    db.run(\n      `UPDATE memories SET status = 'deprecated' WHERE id IN (${placeholders})`,\n      toDeprecate\n    );\n  }\n\n  return { deprecated: toDeprecate.length, scored: rows.length };\n}\n\n// Auto-relation detection — called fire-and-forget from learn()\nasync function autoDetectRelations(\n  newId: number,\n  content: string,\n  getSimilarMemories: (text: string, topN: number, threshold: number) => Promise<Array<{ id: number; content: string; similarity: number }>>,\n  classifyRelation: (a: string, b: string) => Promise<RelationshipType | null>,\n): Promise<void> {\n  try {\n    const { readConfigSync } = await import(\"./config.js\");\n    if (readConfigSync().ltm?.autoRelate === false) return;\n\n    const candidates = await getSimilarMemories(content, 5, 0.6);\n    const others = candidates.filter(c => c.id !== newId);\n    if (!others.length) return;\n\n    await Promise.allSettled(\n      others.map(async (candidate) => {\n        const relType = await classifyRelation(content, candidate.content);\n        if (!relType) return;\n        try {\n          relate({ source_id: newId, target_id: candidate.id, relationship_type: relType });\n        } catch {\n          // Memory may have been deleted between detection and insertion — ignore\n        }\n      })\n    );\n  } catch (err) {\n    process.stderr.write(`[autoDetectRelations] error for memory ${newId}: ${err}\\n`);\n  }\n}\n\nexport function learn(input: LearnInput): LearnResult {\n  const db = getDb();\n\n  // Scrub secrets before any DB write or dedup check\n  const { scrubbed, redactions } = scrubSecrets(input.content);\n  if (redactions.length > 0) {\n    process.stderr.write(`[learn] Scrubbed ${redactions.length} secret(s): ${redactions.join(\", \")}\\n`);\n  }\n  const content = scrubbed;\n\n  const dedupKey = normalizeKey(content);\n  const skipExport = input.skipExport ?? false;\n\n  const existing = db.query<Memory, [string]>(`SELECT * FROM memories WHERE dedup_key=?`).get(dedupKey);\n\n  const actor = input.actor ?? \"mcp:ltm_learn\";","lineStart":200,"lineEnd":319,"totalLines":780,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","time":{"start":1780924936272,"end":1780924936284}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04b3cfa87004f1e2016a26c208424081918d3170cd01f2af08"}},"id":"prt_ea765f04d001Apb1KX4uesmhW5","sessionID":"ses_1589b1327ffe3NF41ZJpTNBQ7B","messageID":"msg_ea765cc190019agoUNAu6yQRpq"}}
