 selected at install time. Implementations: `null` (FTS5 only), `local-hash`\n\n  Line 821: Recall remains FTS5-first; the embedding step is a fallback **and** an enrichment\n\n  Line 822: (pre-rank pass for high-recall queries). Provider is hot-swappable: changing the\n\n  Line 883: Recall results carry provenance; the explainer (C8) surfaces it inline.\n\n  Line 902: ### 8.10 C8 — Recall result explainer\n\n  Line 904: Each result returns a one-line `why_ranked` (e.g. \"FTS5 BM25=4.2 + recency boost +\n\n  Line 990: - New optional fields on recall results: `provenance`, `why_ranked` (C8).\n\n  Line 998: - Recall logic gains a \"rerank with embeddings\" pass for high-recall queries.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/skills/Ltm/SKILL.md:\n  Line 29: 1. **Recall before** — `recall` with natural language (FTS5 + semantic fallback), not bare keywords. Project restore → `context`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/04-configuration.md:\n  Line 16:     \"semanticFallback\": true\n\n  Line 29: | `semanticFallback` | `true` | Fall back to embedding search when FTS returns no results |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/02-how-it-works.md:\n  Line 36:                      |  | memories_fts    | |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/internal/UX-SPEC.md:\n  Line 132: Found 3 memories (FTS5 + 1 semantic):\n\n  Line 138: → ranked by relevance, importance, recency\n\n  Line 170: | FTS5 syntax error      | bubbled SQL error          | `Invalid FTS query. Wrap phrases in quotes.`